WEBVTT

1
00:02:18.674 --> 00:02:21.711
13 metres. You should see it.

2
00:02:34.154 --> 00:02:37.271
Okay. Take her up
and over the bow rail.

3
00:02:37.354 --> 00:02:42.223
Okay. Mir 2. we're going over the bow.
Stay with us.

4
00:03:13.954 --> 00:03:16.070
Okay. quiet. We're rolling.

5
00:03:16.154 --> 00:03:19.829
Seeing her coming out
of the darkness like a ghost ship

6
00:03:19.914 --> 00:03:21.632
still gets me every time.

7
00:03:21.714 --> 00:03:26.310
To see the sad ruin
of the great ship sitting here

8
00:03:26.394 --> 00:03:31.832
where she landed at 2:30
in the morning of April 15. 1912.

9
00:03:31.874 --> 00:03:33.990
after her long fall

10
00:03:34.994 --> 00:03:36.985
from the world above.

11
00:03:37.714 --> 00:03:39.750
You are so full of shit. boss!

12
00:04:07.794 --> 00:04:11.707
Dive six - here we are again
on the deck of Titanic.

13
00:04:11.834 --> 00:04:17.670
21/2 miles down. 3.821 metres.

14
00:04:17.754 --> 00:04:21.030
The pressure outside
is 31/2 tons per square inch.

15
00:04:21.114 --> 00:04:23.423
These windows are nine inches thick.

16
00:04:23.514 --> 00:04:27.348
If they go.
it's sayonara in two microseconds.

17
00:04:27.434 --> 00:04:30.028
All right. Enough of that bullshit.

18
00:04:43.194 --> 00:04:46.425
Put her down on the roof
of the officers' quarters.

19
00:04:46.594 --> 00:04:47.709
Sure.

20
00:04:47.794 --> 00:04:49.432
Okay. Mir 2.

21
00:04:49.514 --> 00:04:53.348
We've landed on the grand staircase.
You guys set to launch?

22
00:04:53.434 --> 00:04:55.994
Yeah. Launching Dunkin now.
Go. Charlie.

23
00:05:03.514 --> 00:05:05.823
- Tether out.
- Tether out.

24
00:05:05.914 --> 00:05:09.907
Okay. Brock.
we're dropping down along the hull.

25
00:05:11.034 --> 00:05:15.550
Roger that. Okay. drop down and
go into the first-class gangway door.

26
00:05:15.634 --> 00:05:19.593
I want you guys working the "D" deck.
reception and the dining saloon.

27
00:05:19.674 --> 00:05:21.505
Copy that.

28
00:05:27.474 --> 00:05:29.112
- Tether out.
- Tether out.

29
00:05:29.194 --> 00:05:31.230
- Now left.
- I'm coming left.

30
00:05:38.354 --> 00:05:40.868
Snoop Dog is on the move.

31
00:05:40.954 --> 00:05:43.343
We're headed down the stairwell.

32
00:05:45.234 --> 00:05:47.304
Okay. Lewis. Drop down to "B" deck.

33
00:05:47.394 --> 00:05:48.622
Okay. "A" deck.

34
00:05:48.714 --> 00:05:50.705
Give me some rope. Captain.

35
00:05:50.794 --> 00:05:51.783
"B" deck. Get in there.

36
00:06:28.474 --> 00:06:30.704
Watch the doorframe.

37
00:06:30.794 --> 00:06:32.512
I see it. I got it.

38
00:06:37.754 --> 00:06:39.631
We're good... Just chill. boss.

39
00:06:53.394 --> 00:06:55.225
Make your turn.

40
00:06:55.314 --> 00:06:58.306
- Cable out. Captain.
- Make your turn.

41
00:06:58.394 --> 00:07:00.703
Brock. we're at the piano.
You copy?

42
00:07:00.794 --> 00:07:02.785
Okay. copy that.

43
00:07:09.674 --> 00:07:12.108
Right there. that's it!

44
00:07:12.194 --> 00:07:15.266
- That's the bedroom door!
- I see it... I see it.

45
00:07:23.754 --> 00:07:24.948
We're in!

46
00:07:25.034 --> 00:07:27.753
We're in. baby. we're there!

47
00:07:27.834 --> 00:07:30.109
That's Hockley's bed.

48
00:07:30.194 --> 00:07:32.754
That's where the son of a bitch slept.

49
00:07:37.874 --> 00:07:40.593
Somebody left the water running.

50
00:07:40.674 --> 00:07:43.234
Hold it. Go back to the right.

51
00:07:49.114 --> 00:07:51.753
That wardrobe door... Get closer.

52
00:07:51.834 --> 00:07:55.144
- You smelling something. boss?
- I wanna see what's under it.

53
00:07:55.234 --> 00:07:56.667
Gimme my hands. man.

54
00:08:01.834 --> 00:08:03.426
All right...!

55
00:08:04.914 --> 00:08:08.509
- Take it easy. It might come apart.
- Okay.

56
00:08:08.594 --> 00:08:09.822
Go! Go. go. go!

57
00:08:09.914 --> 00:08:11.870
Flip it over. flip it over. Go.

58
00:08:11.954 --> 00:08:14.593
Keep going. Go. go. go.

59
00:08:14.674 --> 00:08:15.823
Okay. Drop it.

60
00:08:24.354 --> 00:08:27.710
Oh. baby. baby...
Are you seeing this. boss?

61
00:08:29.714 --> 00:08:31.705
It's payday. boys.

62
00:08:47.434 --> 00:08:49.186
Ka-ching!

63
00:08:49.274 --> 00:08:50.912
We did it. Bobby!

64
00:08:50.994 --> 00:08:53.952
Oh. yeah! Who's the man!

65
00:08:54.034 --> 00:08:55.831
Who's the best. baby?

66
00:08:55.914 --> 00:08:57.313
Say it. say it.

67
00:08:57.394 --> 00:08:59.271
You are. Lewis.

68
00:09:01.514 --> 00:09:03.470
- Bobby. my cigar.
- Right here.

69
00:09:10.714 --> 00:09:12.784
Okay. crack her open.

70
00:09:14.794 --> 00:09:18.548
- Let me get around. Hang on.
- You getting it?

71
00:09:41.194 --> 00:09:43.071
Shit.

72
00:09:43.714 --> 00:09:45.432
No diamond.

73
00:09:45.514 --> 00:09:47.391
You know. boss.

74
00:09:47.474 --> 00:09:52.468
the same thing happened to Geraldo.
and his career never recovered.

75
00:09:54.234 --> 00:09:56.190
Turn the camera off.

76
00:09:56.274 --> 00:10:00.426
Brock. the partners would
like to know how it's going.

77
00:10:00.514 --> 00:10:04.302
Hey. Dave. Barry. Hi.
Look. it wasn't in the safe. but hey

78
00:10:04.394 --> 00:10:08.273
don't worry about it.
There's plenty of places it could be.

79
00:10:08.354 --> 00:10:10.424
The floor debris.
the mother's room...

80
00:10:10.514 --> 00:10:12.903
- Purser's safe on "C" deck.
- Jimmy Hoffa's briefcase.

81
00:10:12.994 --> 00:10:14.632
A dozen other places.

82
00:10:14.714 --> 00:10:17.911
You've got to trust my instincts.
I know we're close.

83
00:10:17.994 --> 00:10:21.430
We just got to go through
a process of elimination.

84
00:10:21.514 --> 00:10:23.505
Hang on a second.

85
00:10:25.474 --> 00:10:27.465
Let me see that.

86
00:10:27.514 --> 00:10:29.391
We might have something here. guys.

87
00:10:30.914 --> 00:10:33.508
Where's the photo of the necklace?

88
00:10:33.554 --> 00:10:36.193
- We'll call you right back.
- Holy...

89
00:10:45.754 --> 00:10:47.745
I'll be goddamned.

90
00:10:48.914 --> 00:10:53.624
Treasure hunter Brock Lovett
is best known for finding Spanish gold...

91
00:10:53.714 --> 00:10:56.547
It's okay. I'll feed you in a minute.

92
00:10:56.634 --> 00:11:01.628
He's chartered a Russian sub to reach
the most famous wreck of all: Titanic.

93
00:11:01.714 --> 00:11:05.707
He's with us live via satellite from
the Keldysh in the North Atlantic.

94
00:11:05.794 --> 00:11:08.308
- Hello. Brock.
- Hello. Tracy.

95
00:11:08.394 --> 00:11:11.192
Everyone knows
the stories of Titanic.

96
00:11:11.274 --> 00:11:14.550
the nobility.
the band playing and all that.

97
00:11:14.634 --> 00:11:18.912
I'm interested in the untold stories.
the secrets deep inside the hull.

98
00:11:18.994 --> 00:11:22.907
We're using robot technology
to go further into the wreck

99
00:11:22.994 --> 00:11:24.950
than anybody's ever done before.

100
00:11:25.034 --> 00:11:28.185
You're at the centre of a controversy

101
00:11:28.274 --> 00:11:32.233
over salvage rights. and ethics.
Many are calling you a grave robber.

102
00:11:32.314 --> 00:11:34.669
Nobody called the recovery
of King Tut "grave robbing".

103
00:11:34.754 --> 00:11:37.393
- What is it?
- Turn that up. dear.

104
00:11:37.474 --> 00:11:40.227
I have museum-trained experts here

105
00:11:40.314 --> 00:11:42.874
making sure these relics
are treated properly.

106
00:11:42.954 --> 00:11:45.912
Look at this drawing
we found just today.

107
00:11:45.994 --> 00:11:49.509
A piece of paper that's been
underwater for 84 years

108
00:11:49.594 --> 00:11:53.223
and my team were able
to preserve it intact.

109
00:11:53.314 --> 00:11:58.183
Should this have remained unseen
at the bottom of the ocean for eternity?

110
00:11:58.274 --> 00:11:59.787
I'll be goddamned.

111
00:12:02.714 --> 00:12:05.672
Brock!
There's a satellite call for you.

112
00:12:05.754 --> 00:12:09.588
Bobby. we're launching.
You see these submersibles going in?

113
00:12:09.674 --> 00:12:12.234
Trust me. buddy.
You wanna take this call.

114
00:12:13.474 --> 00:12:15.430
This better be good.

115
00:12:15.514 --> 00:12:18.472
You gotta speak up.
She's kinda old.

116
00:12:18.554 --> 00:12:20.306
Great.

117
00:12:20.394 --> 00:12:23.466
This is Brock Lovett.
How can I help you. Mrs...?

118
00:12:23.554 --> 00:12:25.670
Calvert. Rose Calvert.

119
00:12:25.754 --> 00:12:27.551
Mrs Calvert?

120
00:12:27.634 --> 00:12:32.788
I was just wondering if you'd found
the "Heart of the Ocean". Mr Lovett.

121
00:12:34.474 --> 00:12:36.704
I said you wanted to take the call.

122
00:12:38.754 --> 00:12:41.188
All right.
You have my attention. Rose.

123
00:12:41.274 --> 00:12:44.186
Can you tell us who the woman
in the picture is?

124
00:12:44.274 --> 00:12:45.787
Oh. yes.

125
00:12:45.874 --> 00:12:48.468
The woman in the picture is me.

126
00:13:03.434 --> 00:13:07.950
She's a goddamned liar! Some nutcase
seeking money or publicity!

127
00:13:08.034 --> 00:13:11.743
God only knows why!
Like that Russian babe. Anaesthesia!

128
00:13:11.834 --> 00:13:13.825
They're inbound!

129
00:13:18.274 --> 00:13:21.869
Rose DeWitt Bukater died on Titanic
when she was 17.

130
00:13:21.954 --> 00:13:23.228
Right.

131
00:13:23.314 --> 00:13:25.782
If she'd lived. she'd be over 100 by now.

132
00:13:25.874 --> 00:13:28.183
101 next month.

133
00:13:28.274 --> 00:13:31.186
So she's a very old goddamned liar!

134
00:13:31.274 --> 00:13:34.107
I've done the background
on this woman

135
00:13:34.194 --> 00:13:37.630
back to the '20s
when she was working as an actress.

136
00:13:37.714 --> 00:13:39.147
An actress!

137
00:13:39.234 --> 00:13:43.193
There's your first clue. Sherlock!
Her name was Rose Dawson back then.

138
00:13:43.274 --> 00:13:48.507
She marries a guy named Calvert.
They move to Cedar Rapids and have kids.

139
00:13:48.594 --> 00:13:51.506
Now Calvert's dead.
and Cedar Rapids. too.

140
00:13:51.594 --> 00:13:54.233
Everybody who knows
about the diamond

141
00:13:54.314 --> 00:13:56.225
is supposed to be dead
or on this boat. but she knows.

142
00:14:08.674 --> 00:14:11.552
Doesn't exactly travel light. does she?

143
00:14:13.474 --> 00:14:15.544
Mrs Calvert. I'm Brock Lovett.

144
00:14:15.634 --> 00:14:17.625
Welcome to the Keldysh.

145
00:14:19.154 --> 00:14:21.031
Let's get her inside.

146
00:14:21.074 --> 00:14:22.393
Hi. Ms Calvert.

147
00:14:22.474 --> 00:14:24.669
- Hi.
- Welcome to the Keldysh.

148
00:14:26.514 --> 00:14:27.993
Hey.

149
00:14:28.074 --> 00:14:29.666
Hey!

150
00:14:35.714 --> 00:14:36.703
Yes?

151
00:14:36.754 --> 00:14:39.587
- Are your staterooms all right?
- Very nice.

152
00:14:39.674 --> 00:14:42.632
Have you met my granddaughter Lizzy?

153
00:14:42.714 --> 00:14:44.670
She takes care of me.

154
00:14:44.754 --> 00:14:47.268
We metjust a few minutes ago.

155
00:14:47.354 --> 00:14:49.788
Remember. Nana? Up on deck?

156
00:14:49.874 --> 00:14:52.308
There. that's nice.

157
00:14:52.394 --> 00:14:54.988
Have to have my pictures when I travel.

158
00:14:55.074 --> 00:14:57.542
Is there anything you'd like?

159
00:14:59.154 --> 00:15:00.587
Yes.

160
00:15:00.674 --> 00:15:03.188
I would like to see my drawing.

161
00:15:15.354 --> 00:15:20.587
Louis XVI wore a fabulous stone.
the Blue Diamond of the Crown.

162
00:15:20.674 --> 00:15:23.586
which disappeared in 1792.

163
00:15:23.674 --> 00:15:27.303
About that time old Louis
lost everything. from the neck up.

164
00:15:27.394 --> 00:15:31.831
The theory goes that
the Crown Diamond was chopped. too.

165
00:15:31.914 --> 00:15:35.987
Recut into a heart shape that became
known as "The Heart of the Ocean".

166
00:15:36.074 --> 00:15:38.349
Today it'd be worth more
than the Hope Diamond.

167
00:15:38.434 --> 00:15:40.743
It was a dreadful. heavy thing.

168
00:15:40.834 --> 00:15:43.587
I only wore it this once.

169
00:15:43.674 --> 00:15:45.869
You actually think this is you. Nana?

170
00:15:45.954 --> 00:15:47.831
It is me. dear.

171
00:15:47.914 --> 00:15:49.905
Wasn't I a dish?

172
00:15:51.274 --> 00:15:53.993
I tracked it down
through insurance records.

173
00:15:54.074 --> 00:15:57.703
An old claim that was settled
under terms of absolute secrecy.

174
00:15:57.794 --> 00:16:02.026
Can you tell me
who the claimant was. Rose?

175
00:16:02.114 --> 00:16:04.230
I imagine someone named Hockley.

176
00:16:04.314 --> 00:16:06.544
Nathan Hockley. that's right.

177
00:16:06.634 --> 00:16:08.590
Pittsburgh steel tycoon.

178
00:16:08.674 --> 00:16:13.464
The claim was for a necklace his son
Caledon bought his fiancée - you -

179
00:16:13.554 --> 00:16:16.387
a week before he sailed on Titanic.

180
00:16:16.474 --> 00:16:19.227
It was filed right after the sinking.

181
00:16:19.314 --> 00:16:23.466
so the diamond had to have
gone down with the ship.

182
00:16:24.914 --> 00:16:26.905
You see the date?

183
00:16:27.554 --> 00:16:29.510
"April 14. 1912."

184
00:16:29.594 --> 00:16:31.983
If your grandmother
is who she says she is.

185
00:16:32.074 --> 00:16:34.952
she was wearing the diamond
the day the Titanic sank.

186
00:16:35.034 --> 00:16:38.390
And that makes you my new best friend.

187
00:16:38.474 --> 00:16:42.911
These are some of the things
we recovered from your stateroom.

188
00:16:44.834 --> 00:16:46.825
This was mine!

189
00:16:47.594 --> 00:16:49.550
How extraordinary!

190
00:16:49.634 --> 00:16:53.627
And it looks the same as it did
the last time I saw it.

191
00:16:58.994 --> 00:17:01.383
The reflection has changed a bit.

192
00:17:17.434 --> 00:17:19.902
Are you ready to go back to Titanic?

193
00:17:23.234 --> 00:17:27.512
Okay. here we go. She hits the berg
on the starboard side. right?

194
00:17:27.594 --> 00:17:32.304
She bumps along. punching holes
along the side. below the waterline.

195
00:17:32.394 --> 00:17:35.989
Then the forward compartments
start to flood.

196
00:17:36.074 --> 00:17:39.191
As the water rises. it spills over
the watertight bulkheads

197
00:17:39.274 --> 00:17:41.868
which don't go any higher
than "E" deck.

198
00:17:41.954 --> 00:17:45.663
So now as the bow goes down.
the stern rises up.

199
00:17:45.754 --> 00:17:48.109
slow at first.
then faster and faster.

200
00:17:48.194 --> 00:17:51.630
until she's got her whole ass
up in the air. A big ass.

201
00:17:51.714 --> 00:17:55.229
We're talking 20.000. 30.000 tons. okay?

202
00:17:55.314 --> 00:17:59.387
The hull's not designed to deal
with that pressure. so what happens?

203
00:17:59.474 --> 00:18:04.707
She splits. right down to the keel.
and the stern falls back level.

204
00:18:04.794 --> 00:18:07.547
As the bow sinks
it pulls the stern vertical

205
00:18:07.634 --> 00:18:09.864
and then finally detaches.

206
00:18:09.954 --> 00:18:14.391
The stern section bobs there
like a cork for a few minutes.

207
00:18:14.474 --> 00:18:17.034
floods. and finally goes under
about 2.20am.

208
00:18:17.114 --> 00:18:20.504
Two hours and 40 minutes
after the collision.

209
00:18:20.594 --> 00:18:25.110
The bow section planes away.
landing about half a mile away.

210
00:18:25.194 --> 00:18:28.231
going 20. 30 knots
when it hits the ocean floor.

211
00:18:30.794 --> 00:18:32.546
Pretty cool. huh?

212
00:18:32.634 --> 00:18:37.754
Thank you for that fine
forensic analysis. Mr Bodine.

213
00:18:37.834 --> 00:18:43.466
Of course. the experience of it was...
somewhat different.

214
00:18:43.554 --> 00:18:45.988
Will you share it with us?

215
00:19:38.394 --> 00:19:40.783
- I'm taking her to rest.
- No.

216
00:19:40.874 --> 00:19:42.865
- Come on. Nana.
- No!

217
00:19:47.274 --> 00:19:49.265
Tape recorder.

218
00:19:50.594 --> 00:19:52.585
Tell us. Rose.

219
00:19:54.674 --> 00:19:56.630
It's been 84 years.

220
00:19:56.714 --> 00:19:58.625
Try to remember anything.

221
00:19:58.714 --> 00:20:00.227
Anything at all.

222
00:20:00.314 --> 00:20:03.943
Do you want to hear this or not.
Mr Lovett?

223
00:20:07.954 --> 00:20:10.946
It's been 84 years

224
00:20:11.674 --> 00:20:15.269
and I can still smell the fresh paint.

225
00:20:17.274 --> 00:20:19.868
The china had never been used.

226
00:20:20.754 --> 00:20:23.222
The sheets had never been slept in.

227
00:20:24.794 --> 00:20:28.184
Titanic was called
"The Ship of Dreams".

228
00:20:30.074 --> 00:20:32.065
And it was.

229
00:20:32.194 --> 00:20:34.185
It really was.

230
00:21:01.474 --> 00:21:04.193
All third-class passengers

231
00:21:04.274 --> 00:21:06.310
with a forward berth.

232
00:21:06.394 --> 00:21:09.466
this way. please.
This queue. Right here.

233
00:21:09.554 --> 00:21:10.782
Big boat. uh?

234
00:21:10.874 --> 00:21:13.104
- Daddy. it's a ship.
- You're right.

235
00:21:42.594 --> 00:21:46.951
Why all the fuss? It doesn't look
any bigger than the Mauretania.

236
00:21:47.034 --> 00:21:50.868
You can be blasé about some things.
Rose. but not about Titanic.

237
00:21:50.954 --> 00:21:52.546
It's 100 feet longer

238
00:21:52.634 --> 00:21:54.590
and far more luxurious.

239
00:21:54.674 --> 00:21:57.586
Your daughter is difficult
to impress. Ruth.

240
00:21:57.674 --> 00:22:00.552
So this is the ship
they say is unsinkable.

241
00:22:00.634 --> 00:22:03.194
God himself could not sink this ship.

242
00:22:03.274 --> 00:22:06.869
Sir. you have to check your baggage
through the main terminal.

243
00:22:06.954 --> 00:22:10.185
I put my faith in you. good sir.
Now kindly see my man.

244
00:22:10.274 --> 00:22:12.230
Yes. sir. My pleasure. sir.

245
00:22:12.314 --> 00:22:13.463
Right.

246
00:22:13.554 --> 00:22:16.193
All the trunks from that car there.

247
00:22:16.274 --> 00:22:19.505
12 from here. and the safe.

248
00:22:19.594 --> 00:22:22.347
to the Parlour Suite. rooms B52. 54. 56.

249
00:22:23.914 --> 00:22:25.870
Ladies...

250
00:22:25.954 --> 00:22:27.592
Better hurry.

251
00:22:32.354 --> 00:22:34.822
- My coat?
- I have it. miss.

252
00:22:36.194 --> 00:22:40.824
All third-class passengers
queue here for health inspection.

253
00:22:40.914 --> 00:22:42.233
Chin up.

254
00:22:46.954 --> 00:22:50.708
Welcome aboard. ma'am.
Welcome to Titanic.

255
00:22:50.794 --> 00:22:54.184
It was the ship of dreams
- to everyone else.

256
00:22:55.114 --> 00:22:57.674
To me it was a slave ship

257
00:22:57.754 --> 00:23:01.349
taking me back to America in chains.

258
00:23:01.434 --> 00:23:05.791
Outwardly I was everything
a well-brought-up girl should be.

259
00:23:05.874 --> 00:23:08.183
Inside. I was screaming.

260
00:23:23.754 --> 00:23:26.985
Jack. you are pazzo.
You bet everything we have.

261
00:23:27.074 --> 00:23:30.191
When you got nothing.
you got nothing to lose.

262
00:23:31.634 --> 00:23:36.230
You moron.
I can't believe you bet our tickets.

263
00:23:37.034 --> 00:23:38.023
Sven?

264
00:23:58.794 --> 00:24:01.308
All right... moment of truth.

265
00:24:01.674 --> 00:24:04.188
Somebody's life's about to change.

266
00:24:04.274 --> 00:24:05.229
Fabrizio?

267
00:24:07.234 --> 00:24:08.223
Niente.

268
00:24:08.274 --> 00:24:09.309
Niente.

269
00:24:10.794 --> 00:24:12.386
Olaf?

270
00:24:12.674 --> 00:24:13.743
Nothing.

271
00:24:13.834 --> 00:24:15.426
Sven?

272
00:24:17.714 --> 00:24:20.308
Uh-oh. Two pair.

273
00:24:20.514 --> 00:24:22.470
I'm sorry. Fabrizio.

274
00:24:22.554 --> 00:24:24.829
"Sorry"? You bet all the money!

275
00:24:24.914 --> 00:24:28.623
I'm sorry. You're not gonna see
your mom for a long time.

276
00:24:28.714 --> 00:24:31.990
Cos we're going to America!
Full house. boys!

277
00:24:32.074 --> 00:24:33.587
Whoa!

278
00:24:33.674 --> 00:24:34.948
Yeah!

279
00:24:35.034 --> 00:24:37.070
Dio mio. grazie!

280
00:24:44.274 --> 00:24:45.866
Come on!

281
00:24:45.954 --> 00:24:47.148
Figlio di puttana!

282
00:24:47.234 --> 00:24:48.906
I'm going home!

283
00:24:51.634 --> 00:24:52.828
I'm going home!

284
00:24:52.914 --> 00:24:54.870
I go to America!

285
00:24:54.954 --> 00:24:56.103
No. mate.

286
00:24:56.194 --> 00:24:58.913
Titanic go to America. in five minutes.

287
00:25:00.034 --> 00:25:02.389
Come on! Come on. here!

288
00:25:02.474 --> 00:25:04.544
Andiamo!

289
00:25:04.634 --> 00:25:08.309
We're riding in high style now!
We're a couple of swells!

290
00:25:08.394 --> 00:25:11.192
Practically goddamn royalty.
ragazzo mio!

291
00:25:11.274 --> 00:25:14.186
You see. it's my destino!

292
00:25:14.274 --> 00:25:16.663
I go to America to be millionario!

293
00:25:16.754 --> 00:25:18.312
Whoa! Whoa!

294
00:25:18.394 --> 00:25:19.986
Bastardo!

295
00:25:20.074 --> 00:25:24.192
- You're pazzo!
- Maybe. but I've got the tickets!

296
00:25:24.274 --> 00:25:26.469
Come on. I thought you were fast!

297
00:25:26.554 --> 00:25:30.593
- Aspetta!
- Wait! Hey. wait!

298
00:25:30.674 --> 00:25:33.063
We're passengers! Passengers!

299
00:25:33.914 --> 00:25:37.190
- Have you been through the inspection?
- Of course!

300
00:25:37.274 --> 00:25:40.107
Anyway. we don't have lice.
We're Americans.

301
00:25:40.194 --> 00:25:42.992
Right. Come aboard.

302
00:25:45.834 --> 00:25:49.031
We're the luckiest sons of bitches
in the world!

303
00:25:57.074 --> 00:25:58.712
Goodbye!

304
00:26:02.754 --> 00:26:05.314
- You know somebody?
- That's not the point.

305
00:26:05.394 --> 00:26:09.865
- Goodbye! I'll miss you!
- Goodbye! I will never forget you!

306
00:26:56.434 --> 00:26:58.425
Go left. darling.

307
00:27:03.114 --> 00:27:04.866
G60. G60...

308
00:27:04.954 --> 00:27:06.945
Excuse me. ma'am.

309
00:27:09.114 --> 00:27:11.105
Oh. right here.

310
00:27:11.394 --> 00:27:14.625
Hey. how you doing?
Jack. Nice to meet you.

311
00:27:14.714 --> 00:27:18.468
I'm Jack Dawson. Nice to meet you.
How you doing?

312
00:27:18.554 --> 00:27:21.022
Who says you get top bunk. huh?

313
00:27:22.634 --> 00:27:24.590
Where's Sven?

314
00:27:24.674 --> 00:27:29.873
This is your private deck. sir.
Would you be requiring anything?

315
00:27:29.954 --> 00:27:31.865
- Mm-mm.
- Excuse me.

316
00:27:31.954 --> 00:27:36.470
- This one?
- No... It had a lot of faces on it.

317
00:27:36.554 --> 00:27:38.545
This is the one.

318
00:27:39.074 --> 00:27:41.634
Would you like all of them out. miss?

319
00:27:41.714 --> 00:27:44.786
Yes... We need a little colour
in this room.

320
00:27:47.114 --> 00:27:49.548
Put it in there. in the wardrobe.

321
00:27:49.634 --> 00:27:52.512
God. not those finger paintings again!

322
00:27:52.594 --> 00:27:53.993
Waste of money!

323
00:27:54.074 --> 00:27:56.110
The difference between Cal's taste
and mine

324
00:27:56.194 --> 00:27:58.913
is that I have some.
They're fascinating.

325
00:27:58.994 --> 00:28:02.111
Like being inside a dream
or something.

326
00:28:02.194 --> 00:28:03.991
There's truth. but no logic.

327
00:28:04.074 --> 00:28:07.032
- What's the artist's name?
- Something Picasso.

328
00:28:07.114 --> 00:28:11.027
"Something Picasso".
He won't amount to a thing. Trust me.

329
00:28:11.114 --> 00:28:14.663
- Put the Degas in the bedroom.
- At least they were cheap.

330
00:28:14.754 --> 00:28:16.745
Put it in the wardrobe.

331
00:28:21.274 --> 00:28:25.233
At Cherbourg. a woman
came aboard named Margaret Brown.

332
00:28:25.314 --> 00:28:27.225
We all called her Molly.

333
00:28:27.314 --> 00:28:31.193
History would call her
"The Unsinkable Molly Brown".

334
00:28:31.274 --> 00:28:35.665
I wasn't about to wait all day. sonny.
Here. think you can manage?

335
00:28:35.754 --> 00:28:39.190
Her husband had struck gold
someplace out west

336
00:28:39.274 --> 00:28:42.471
and she was what Mother called
"new money".

337
00:28:42.554 --> 00:28:46.752
By next afternoon we were steaming
west from the coast of Ireland

338
00:28:46.834 --> 00:28:50.827
with nothing out ahead of us but ocean.

339
00:28:56.834 --> 00:28:59.871
Take her to sea. Mr Murdoch.

340
00:28:59.954 --> 00:29:02.866
- Let's stretch her legs.
- Yes. sir.

341
00:29:04.714 --> 00:29:07.786
- All ahead full. Mr Moody.
- Very good. sir.

342
00:29:12.274 --> 00:29:13.502
All ahead full.

343
00:29:13.594 --> 00:29:15.744
All ahead full!

344
00:29:15.834 --> 00:29:17.825
Come on. lads. Step lively.

345
00:29:35.354 --> 00:29:38.710
Let's stoke them right up!
We're going full ahead!

346
00:30:32.994 --> 00:30:34.985
21 knots. sir.

347
00:30:42.954 --> 00:30:45.514
Hey. look. look. look!
Look. look!

348
00:30:47.754 --> 00:30:49.187
See it?

349
00:30:52.354 --> 00:30:54.424
There's another one! See him?

350
00:31:03.794 --> 00:31:05.512
Look at that one!

351
00:31:05.594 --> 00:31:07.505
Look at him jump!

352
00:31:07.594 --> 00:31:08.310
Whoo-hoo!

353
00:31:29.234 --> 00:31:30.952
Whoo!

354
00:31:31.594 --> 00:31:34.154
I can see the Statue of Liberty already!

355
00:31:34.234 --> 00:31:35.986
Very small. of course.

356
00:31:38.354 --> 00:31:42.188
I'm the king of the world!

357
00:32:25.994 --> 00:32:28.713
She is the largest moving object
ever made by the hand of man

358
00:32:28.794 --> 00:32:30.591
in all history.

359
00:32:30.674 --> 00:32:33.632
Our master shipbuilder. Mr Andrews.

360
00:32:33.714 --> 00:32:35.193
designed her.

361
00:32:35.274 --> 00:32:37.071
I knocked her together

362
00:32:37.154 --> 00:32:39.543
but the idea was Mr Ismay's.

363
00:32:39.634 --> 00:32:42.910
He envisioned a steamer
so grand in scale

364
00:32:42.994 --> 00:32:46.191
that its supremacy
would never be challenged.

365
00:32:46.274 --> 00:32:47.787
And here she is

366
00:32:47.874 --> 00:32:49.944
willed into solid reality.

367
00:32:50.034 --> 00:32:51.945
Hear. hear.

368
00:32:52.034 --> 00:32:53.945
Salmon.

369
00:32:56.794 --> 00:33:00.309
You know I don't like that. Rose.

370
00:33:02.394 --> 00:33:04.305
She knows.

371
00:33:05.634 --> 00:33:10.071
We'll both have the lamb. rare.
with very little mint sauce.

372
00:33:10.154 --> 00:33:12.622
You like lamb. right. sweet pea?

373
00:33:14.394 --> 00:33:17.306
Are you gonna cut her meat
for her. too. Cal?

374
00:33:20.154 --> 00:33:24.147
Hey. who thought of the name
"Titanic"? Was it you. Bruce?

375
00:33:24.234 --> 00:33:25.713
Yes. actually.

376
00:33:25.794 --> 00:33:30.504
I wanted to convey sheer size.
and the size means stability.

377
00:33:30.594 --> 00:33:34.553
luxury. and. above all. strength.

378
00:33:34.634 --> 00:33:37.068
Do you know of Dr Freud. Mr Ismay?

379
00:33:37.154 --> 00:33:41.432
His ideas about male preoccupation
with size might interest you.

380
00:33:42.754 --> 00:33:46.144
- What's gotten into you?
- Excuse me.

381
00:33:49.314 --> 00:33:51.225
I do apologise.

382
00:33:51.394 --> 00:33:53.510
She's a pistol. Cal.
Hope you can handle her.

383
00:33:53.594 --> 00:33:57.906
Well. I may have to start minding
what she reads. Mrs Brown.

384
00:33:57.994 --> 00:34:01.350
Freud... who is he?
Is he a passenger?

385
00:34:02.434 --> 00:34:05.471
...turns the propeller.

386
00:34:05.554 --> 00:34:07.545
makes these waves.

387
00:34:08.114 --> 00:34:10.105
makes them spin.

388
00:34:13.114 --> 00:34:15.548
The ship is nice. uh?

389
00:34:15.634 --> 00:34:18.546
- Yeah. it's an Irish ship.
- Is English. no?

390
00:34:18.634 --> 00:34:22.991
No. it was built in Ireland.
15.000 Irishmen built this ship.

391
00:34:23.074 --> 00:34:24.666
That's typical.

392
00:34:24.754 --> 00:34:28.463
First-class dogs come down here
to take a shite.

393
00:34:28.554 --> 00:34:30.510
It lets us know where we rank.

394
00:34:30.594 --> 00:34:32.585
Like we could forget?

395
00:34:33.114 --> 00:34:35.070
I'm Tommy Ryan.

396
00:34:35.154 --> 00:34:37.429
- Jack Dawson.
- Fabrizio.

397
00:34:37.514 --> 00:34:41.587
Hi. Do you make any money
with your drawings?

398
00:34:50.194 --> 00:34:55.268
Oh. forget it. boyo. You'd as like
have angels fly out of your arse

399
00:34:55.354 --> 00:34:57.743
as get next to the likes of her.

400
00:35:19.234 --> 00:35:23.386
I saw my whole life
as if I'd already lived it.

401
00:35:23.474 --> 00:35:27.149
an endless parade of parties
and cotillions.

402
00:35:27.234 --> 00:35:29.225
yachts and polo matches.

403
00:35:29.994 --> 00:35:34.704
Always the same narrow people.
the same mindless chatter.

404
00:35:34.794 --> 00:35:38.753
I felt like I was standing
at a great precipice

405
00:35:38.834 --> 00:35:41.394
with no-one to pull me back.

406
00:35:41.474 --> 00:35:45.626
No-one who cared. or even noticed.

407
00:37:30.714 --> 00:37:32.033
Don't do it.

408
00:37:32.114 --> 00:37:34.025
Stay back.

409
00:37:34.114 --> 00:37:36.230
Don't come any closer.

410
00:37:36.994 --> 00:37:38.950
Come on.

411
00:37:39.034 --> 00:37:41.946
- Gimme your hand. I'll pull you back.
- No!

412
00:37:42.034 --> 00:37:44.309
Stay where you are. I mean it.

413
00:37:45.274 --> 00:37:47.265
I'll let go.

414
00:37:56.434 --> 00:37:58.425
No. you won't.

415
00:37:59.434 --> 00:38:02.187
What do you mean. no. I won't?

416
00:38:02.274 --> 00:38:05.869
Don't presume to tell me
what I will and will not do.

417
00:38:05.954 --> 00:38:07.910
Well. you would've done it already.

418
00:38:07.994 --> 00:38:10.462
You're distracting me. Go away.

419
00:38:10.554 --> 00:38:12.033
I can't.

420
00:38:12.114 --> 00:38:14.344
I'm involved now.

421
00:38:14.434 --> 00:38:18.222
You let go and I'm gonna
have to jump in there after you.

422
00:38:19.434 --> 00:38:22.187
Don't be absurd. You'll be killed.

423
00:38:22.274 --> 00:38:25.903
- I'm a good swimmer.
- The fall alone would kill you.

424
00:38:25.994 --> 00:38:29.304
It would hurt.
I'm not saying it wouldn't.

425
00:38:29.394 --> 00:38:33.353
But I'm more concerned
about that water being so cold.

426
00:38:39.434 --> 00:38:41.231
How cold?

427
00:38:41.314 --> 00:38:44.624
Freezing.
Maybe a couple of degrees over.

428
00:38:47.914 --> 00:38:50.109
You ever. uh...

429
00:38:50.194 --> 00:38:52.424
Ever been to Wisconsin?

430
00:38:54.834 --> 00:38:56.153
What?

431
00:38:56.234 --> 00:38:58.623
They have some of the coldest winters.

432
00:38:58.714 --> 00:39:01.751
I grew up there. near Chippewa Falls.

433
00:39:01.834 --> 00:39:05.588
When I was a kid.
me and my father went ice fishing

434
00:39:05.674 --> 00:39:07.551
out on Lake Wissota.

435
00:39:07.634 --> 00:39:09.511
Ice fishing is where you...

436
00:39:09.594 --> 00:39:11.824
I know what ice fishing is!

437
00:39:11.914 --> 00:39:13.711
Sorry.

438
00:39:14.794 --> 00:39:18.469
You just seem like. you know.
kind of an indoor girl.

439
00:39:20.274 --> 00:39:22.424
Anyway. I. uh...

440
00:39:22.514 --> 00:39:24.789
I fell through some thin ice.

441
00:39:24.874 --> 00:39:27.468
And I'm telling you

442
00:39:27.554 --> 00:39:30.751
water that cold. like right down there.

443
00:39:30.834 --> 00:39:34.713
it hits you like a thousand knives
stabbing you all over.

444
00:39:34.794 --> 00:39:37.388
You can't breathe...

445
00:39:38.434 --> 00:39:40.345
You can't think...

446
00:39:40.434 --> 00:39:42.994
At least not about anything
but the pain.

447
00:39:44.474 --> 00:39:49.150
Which is why I'm not looking forward
to jumping in there after you.

448
00:39:49.234 --> 00:39:50.826
Like I said.

449
00:39:52.594 --> 00:39:54.585
I don't have a choice.

450
00:39:58.154 --> 00:40:02.909
I'm hoping you'll come back
over the rail and get me off the hook here.

451
00:40:02.994 --> 00:40:04.985
You're crazy.

452
00:40:05.514 --> 00:40:08.074
That's what everybody says. but...

453
00:40:08.634 --> 00:40:13.708
With all due respect. miss. I'm not the one
hanging off the back of a ship.

454
00:40:13.794 --> 00:40:15.750
Come on.

455
00:40:15.834 --> 00:40:18.553
Come on. gimme your hand.

456
00:40:18.634 --> 00:40:21.467
You don't wanna do this.

457
00:40:33.034 --> 00:40:34.626
Whew!

458
00:40:35.034 --> 00:40:36.990
I'm Jack Dawson.

459
00:40:37.074 --> 00:40:38.951
Rose DeWitt Bukater.

460
00:40:39.034 --> 00:40:41.594
I'll have to get you
to write that down!

461
00:40:43.754 --> 00:40:45.312
Come on.

462
00:40:50.034 --> 00:40:52.912
I got you! Come on!

463
00:40:52.994 --> 00:40:54.950
Come on!

464
00:40:58.394 --> 00:40:59.747
Help! Please!

465
00:40:59.834 --> 00:41:01.825
Help! Please!

466
00:41:03.074 --> 00:41:05.634
- Please help me!
- Listen! Listen to me!

467
00:41:05.714 --> 00:41:07.386
I've got you. I won't let go.

468
00:41:07.474 --> 00:41:09.669
Now pull yourself up. Come on!

469
00:41:12.234 --> 00:41:13.144
Come on.

470
00:41:13.194 --> 00:41:14.673
That's right.

471
00:41:14.754 --> 00:41:17.143
You can do it.

472
00:41:20.994 --> 00:41:22.393
I got you.

473
00:41:27.154 --> 00:41:30.112
What's all this?

474
00:41:34.754 --> 00:41:38.110
You stand back!
And don't move an inch!

475
00:41:39.034 --> 00:41:40.990
Fetch the master-at-arms!

476
00:41:41.074 --> 00:41:43.030
Care for a brandy?

477
00:41:43.114 --> 00:41:45.753
This is completely unacceptable!

478
00:41:45.834 --> 00:41:49.065
How dare you put your hands
on my fiancée!

479
00:41:49.154 --> 00:41:51.384
- Look at me. you filth!
- Cal...

480
00:41:51.474 --> 00:41:55.831
- What do you think you were doing?
- Cal. stop! It was an accident.

481
00:41:55.914 --> 00:41:57.791
An accident?

482
00:41:57.874 --> 00:41:59.307
It was.

483
00:41:59.394 --> 00:42:01.464
Stupid. really.

484
00:42:01.554 --> 00:42:04.626
I was leaning over and I slipped.

485
00:42:06.114 --> 00:42:10.551
I was leaning far over to see the. uh...

486
00:42:10.634 --> 00:42:11.987
uh...

487
00:42:12.074 --> 00:42:13.063
the. uh...

488
00:42:13.154 --> 00:42:16.112
- Propellers?
- Propellers. And I slipped.

489
00:42:16.194 --> 00:42:20.346
I would have gone overboard.
but Mr Dawson here saved me

490
00:42:20.434 --> 00:42:23.028
and almost went over himself.

491
00:42:23.114 --> 00:42:27.505
- She wanted to see the propellers!
- Women and machinery do not mix.

492
00:42:27.594 --> 00:42:30.791
Was that the way of it?

493
00:42:32.074 --> 00:42:34.588
Yeah. Yeah. that was pretty much it.

494
00:42:34.674 --> 00:42:38.269
The boy's a hero. then.
Good for you. son. Well done.

495
00:42:38.354 --> 00:42:40.424
So it's all's well. and. uh...

496
00:42:40.514 --> 00:42:42.470
back to our brandy. eh?

497
00:42:42.554 --> 00:42:46.547
Look at you. You must be freezing.
Let's get you inside.

498
00:42:46.634 --> 00:42:49.068
Perhaps a little something for the boy?

499
00:42:51.034 --> 00:42:52.433
Of course.

500
00:42:52.514 --> 00:42:55.506
Mr Lovejoy. I think a 20 should do it.

501
00:42:55.634 --> 00:42:59.229
Is that the going rate
for saving the woman you love?

502
00:43:00.834 --> 00:43:03.507
Rose is displeased. What to do...

503
00:43:04.754 --> 00:43:05.982
I know.

504
00:43:07.834 --> 00:43:11.907
Perhaps you could join us
for dinner tomorrow evening

505
00:43:11.994 --> 00:43:15.430
to regale our group with...
your heroic tale.

506
00:43:18.314 --> 00:43:20.191
Sure. Count me in.

507
00:43:20.274 --> 00:43:23.186
Good. Settled. then.

508
00:43:23.274 --> 00:43:26.391
- This should be interesting.
- Mmm.

509
00:43:33.994 --> 00:43:36.383
Can I. uh... bum a smoke?

510
00:43:43.834 --> 00:43:46.109
You'll want to tie those.

511
00:43:48.554 --> 00:43:50.112
It's interesting.

512
00:43:50.194 --> 00:43:52.549
The young lady slips so suddenly

513
00:43:52.634 --> 00:43:57.310
and you still had time to remove
your jacket and your shoes.

514
00:44:11.034 --> 00:44:13.229
I know you've been melancholy.

515
00:44:14.074 --> 00:44:16.065
I don't pretend to know why.

516
00:44:18.514 --> 00:44:20.630
I intended to save this

517
00:44:20.714 --> 00:44:23.672
until the engagement gala

518
00:44:24.234 --> 00:44:26.225
next week.

519
00:44:26.674 --> 00:44:29.029
But... I thought...

520
00:44:29.114 --> 00:44:30.706
tonight.

521
00:44:31.754 --> 00:44:33.745
Good gracious!

522
00:44:33.834 --> 00:44:35.870
A reminder of my feelings for you.

523
00:44:35.954 --> 00:44:37.228
Is it a...?

524
00:44:37.314 --> 00:44:39.066
Diamond? Yes.

525
00:44:41.434 --> 00:44:43.425
56 carats to be exact.

526
00:44:46.314 --> 00:44:51.832
It was worn by Louis XVI.
and they called it "Le Coeur de la Mer".

527
00:44:51.914 --> 00:44:54.508
The Heart of the Ocean.

528
00:44:59.874 --> 00:45:01.830
It's overwhelming.

529
00:45:01.914 --> 00:45:03.905
Well. it's for royalty.

530
00:45:04.834 --> 00:45:06.825
We are royalty. Rose.

531
00:45:10.234 --> 00:45:13.704
You know. there's nothing
I couldn't give you.

532
00:45:13.794 --> 00:45:16.467
There's nothing I'd deny you

533
00:45:16.954 --> 00:45:19.343
if you would not deny me.

534
00:45:21.714 --> 00:45:24.353
Oh. open your heart to me. Rose.

535
00:45:39.714 --> 00:45:44.310
Well. I've been on my own
since I was 15. since my folks died.

536
00:45:44.394 --> 00:45:48.353
I had no close kin
in that part of the country.

537
00:45:48.434 --> 00:45:51.506
So I left and I haven't been back since.

538
00:45:51.594 --> 00:45:55.587
You could just call me a tumbleweed
blowing in the wind.

539
00:45:56.034 --> 00:46:00.312
Well. Rose. we've walked about a mile
around this boat deck

540
00:46:00.394 --> 00:46:04.706
and chewed over how great
the weather's been and how I grew up.

541
00:46:04.794 --> 00:46:09.185
but I reckon that's not
why you came to talk to me. is it?

542
00:46:09.274 --> 00:46:11.993
- Mr Dawson. I...
- Jack.

543
00:46:12.074 --> 00:46:13.553
Jack.

544
00:46:13.634 --> 00:46:16.102
I want to thank you for what you did.

545
00:46:16.914 --> 00:46:21.226
Notjust for... for pulling me back.
but for your discretion.

546
00:46:21.314 --> 00:46:23.032
You're welcome.

547
00:46:23.114 --> 00:46:26.823
Look. I know what
you must be thinking.

548
00:46:28.194 --> 00:46:30.150
Poor little rich girl.

549
00:46:30.234 --> 00:46:32.543
What does she know about misery?

550
00:46:32.634 --> 00:46:35.467
No... No. that's not what I was thinking.

551
00:46:35.554 --> 00:46:39.149
I was thinking
what could have happened to this girl

552
00:46:39.234 --> 00:46:41.873
to make her think she had no way out.

553
00:46:43.674 --> 00:46:45.471
Well. I...

554
00:46:45.874 --> 00:46:49.230
It was everything.
It was my whole world

555
00:46:49.314 --> 00:46:51.225
and all the people in it.

556
00:46:51.314 --> 00:46:55.910
The inertia of my life... plunging
ahead. and me powerless to stop it.

557
00:46:55.994 --> 00:46:58.349
God! Look at that thing!

558
00:46:58.434 --> 00:47:01.267
You would've gone
straight to the bottom.

559
00:47:01.354 --> 00:47:03.948
500 invitations have gone out.

560
00:47:04.234 --> 00:47:07.829
All of Philadelphia society
will be there.

561
00:47:07.914 --> 00:47:11.429
and all the while I feel
I'm standing in a crowded room

562
00:47:11.514 --> 00:47:14.984
screaming at the top of my lungs.
and no-one even looks up.

563
00:47:15.634 --> 00:47:17.545
Do you love him?

564
00:47:18.634 --> 00:47:20.352
Pardon me?

565
00:47:20.434 --> 00:47:22.425
Do you love him?

566
00:47:22.514 --> 00:47:25.028
You shouldn't be asking me this.

567
00:47:25.114 --> 00:47:27.833
It's a simple question.
Do you love the guy or not?

568
00:47:29.554 --> 00:47:33.672
- This is not a suitable conversation.
- Can't you just answer the question?

569
00:47:36.034 --> 00:47:39.788
This is absurd. You don't know me
and I don't know you.

570
00:47:39.874 --> 00:47:42.946
and we are not having this conversation.

571
00:47:43.034 --> 00:47:46.390
You are rude and uncouth
and... I am leaving now.

572
00:47:46.474 --> 00:47:49.272
Jack... Mr Dawson.
it's been a pleasure.

573
00:47:49.354 --> 00:47:51.743
I sought you out to thank you...

574
00:47:51.834 --> 00:47:55.270
- And you insulted me.
- You deserved it.

575
00:47:55.354 --> 00:47:57.345
- Right.
- Right.

576
00:47:59.674 --> 00:48:02.552
- I thought you were leaving.
- I am.

577
00:48:03.674 --> 00:48:05.665
You are so annoying!

578
00:48:05.754 --> 00:48:07.267
Wait.

579
00:48:07.354 --> 00:48:10.949
I don't have to leave.
This is my part of the ship.

580
00:48:11.034 --> 00:48:12.786
You leave.

581
00:48:12.874 --> 00:48:16.310
Well. well. well!
Now who's being rude?

582
00:48:19.354 --> 00:48:23.347
What is this stupid thing
you're carrying around?

583
00:48:23.474 --> 00:48:26.671
So what are you?
An artist or something?

584
00:48:27.274 --> 00:48:30.789
Well... these are rather good.

585
00:48:34.034 --> 00:48:37.344
They're. uh...
they're very good. actually.

586
00:48:44.594 --> 00:48:47.108
Jack. this is exquisite work.

587
00:48:47.194 --> 00:48:50.709
- They didn't like them in old Paris.
- Paris?!

588
00:48:50.794 --> 00:48:54.423
You do get around. for a poor...

589
00:48:55.514 --> 00:48:59.473
Well. uh. uh.
a person of limited means.

590
00:48:59.554 --> 00:49:01.784
A poor guy. You can say it.

591
00:49:04.834 --> 00:49:06.426
Well. well. well!

592
00:49:09.674 --> 00:49:11.949
And these were drawn from life?

593
00:49:15.234 --> 00:49:17.543
That's the good thing about Paris.

594
00:49:17.634 --> 00:49:21.229
Lots of girls
willing to take their clothes off.

595
00:49:24.834 --> 00:49:26.825
You liked this woman.

596
00:49:26.914 --> 00:49:29.428
You used her several times.

597
00:49:30.474 --> 00:49:34.945
Well. she had beautiful hands.
you see?

598
00:49:35.034 --> 00:49:38.231
I think you must have had
a love affair with her.

599
00:49:38.314 --> 00:49:39.303
No. no. no.

600
00:49:39.394 --> 00:49:41.624
Just with her hands.

601
00:49:41.714 --> 00:49:44.148
She was a one-legged prostitute.

602
00:49:44.234 --> 00:49:45.713
See?

603
00:49:48.914 --> 00:49:50.711
Oh!

604
00:49:51.554 --> 00:49:54.387
She had a good sense of humour.
though.

605
00:49:56.234 --> 00:49:57.826
And this lady...

606
00:49:57.914 --> 00:50:02.544
She used to sit at this bar every night

607
00:50:02.634 --> 00:50:06.627
wearing all her jewellery.
waiting for her long-lost love.

608
00:50:07.834 --> 00:50:09.950
Called her Madame Bijoux.

609
00:50:10.034 --> 00:50:13.663
See how her clothes
are all moth-eaten?

610
00:50:13.754 --> 00:50:16.632
Well. you have a gift. Jack.

611
00:50:16.714 --> 00:50:18.147
You do.

612
00:50:18.234 --> 00:50:19.587
You see people.

613
00:50:19.674 --> 00:50:21.790
I see you.

614
00:50:23.674 --> 00:50:25.107
And?

615
00:50:25.194 --> 00:50:27.867
You wouldn't have jumped.

616
00:50:31.834 --> 00:50:36.146
But the purpose of university
is to find a suitable husband.

617
00:50:36.234 --> 00:50:38.145
Rose has already done that.

618
00:50:38.234 --> 00:50:40.907
Here comes that vulgar Brown woman.

619
00:50:40.994 --> 00:50:43.633
Quickly. get up before she sits with us.

620
00:50:43.714 --> 00:50:45.067
Hello. girls.

621
00:50:45.154 --> 00:50:49.147
- I was hoping I'd catch you at tea.
- We're awfully sorry you missed it.

622
00:50:49.234 --> 00:50:51.953
The Countess and I
were just off to the boat deck.

623
00:50:52.034 --> 00:50:54.992
What a lovely idea.
I need to catch up on my gossip.

624
00:50:58.034 --> 00:50:59.831
Countess.

625
00:51:01.034 --> 00:51:04.151
So you've not yet lit
the last four boilers?

626
00:51:04.234 --> 00:51:07.351
I don't see the need.
We are making excellent time.

627
00:51:07.434 --> 00:51:09.994
The press knows the size of Titanic.

628
00:51:10.234 --> 00:51:13.306
Now I want them to marvel at her speed.

629
00:51:13.394 --> 00:51:16.386
We must give them
something new to print.

630
00:51:17.034 --> 00:51:19.468
This maiden voyage of Titanic

631
00:51:19.554 --> 00:51:21.465
must make headlines.

632
00:51:21.554 --> 00:51:25.229
Mr Ismay. I would prefer
not to push the engines

633
00:51:25.314 --> 00:51:27.987
until they've been properly run in.

634
00:51:28.074 --> 00:51:33.307
Of course. I'm just a passenger.
I leave it to you to decide what's best.

635
00:51:33.394 --> 00:51:37.467
But a glorious end to your final trip
if we arrive on Tuesday night

636
00:51:37.554 --> 00:51:40.273
and surprise them all.
Make the morning papers.

637
00:51:40.354 --> 00:51:42.822
Retire with a bang. eh. EJ?

638
00:51:45.594 --> 00:51:47.585
Good man.

639
00:51:48.434 --> 00:51:52.109
Well. after that I worked
on a squid boat in Monterey.

640
00:51:52.194 --> 00:51:54.628
Then I went to the pier in Santa Monica

641
00:51:54.714 --> 00:51:58.627
and started doing portraits there
for 10 cents apiece.

642
00:51:58.674 --> 00:52:02.553
Why can't I be like you. Jack?
Just head out for the horizon

643
00:52:02.634 --> 00:52:04.625
whenever I feel like it.

644
00:52:05.354 --> 00:52:08.391
Say we'll go there sometime to that pier

645
00:52:08.474 --> 00:52:10.510
even if we only just talk about it.

646
00:52:10.594 --> 00:52:12.152
No. we'll do it.

647
00:52:12.234 --> 00:52:15.431
We'll drink cheap beer.
Ride on the roller coaster.

648
00:52:15.514 --> 00:52:18.426
Then we'll ride horses on the beach

649
00:52:18.514 --> 00:52:22.905
right in the surf. But like a real cowboy.
Not that side-saddle stuff.

650
00:52:24.474 --> 00:52:26.465
You mean. one leg on each side?

651
00:52:26.554 --> 00:52:27.953
Yeah.

652
00:52:28.034 --> 00:52:31.310
- Can you show me?
- Sure. If you like.

653
00:52:32.314 --> 00:52:35.943
- Teach me to ride like a man.
- And chew tobacco like a man.

654
00:52:37.354 --> 00:52:39.584
And spit like a man!

655
00:52:39.674 --> 00:52:41.392
They didn't teach you that?

656
00:52:41.474 --> 00:52:42.873
No!

657
00:52:42.954 --> 00:52:44.910
Come on. I'll show you.

658
00:52:44.994 --> 00:52:47.064
I'll show you how. Come on.

659
00:52:47.154 --> 00:52:49.873
Jack! No! Jack! No!

660
00:52:49.954 --> 00:52:52.024
Wait. Jack. No. Jack.

661
00:52:52.114 --> 00:52:55.345
- I couldn't possibly. Jack.
- Watch closely.

662
00:52:56.674 --> 00:52:59.313
- That's disgusting!
- Your turn.

663
00:53:01.834 --> 00:53:03.108
Pitiful!

664
00:53:03.194 --> 00:53:07.631
You really gotta hawk it back.
Use your arms. Arc your neck.

665
00:53:08.634 --> 00:53:11.194
See the range on that thing?

666
00:53:11.274 --> 00:53:13.469
Okay. go.

667
00:53:16.474 --> 00:53:21.423
You gotta work on it. Really try
and hawk it up and get some body to it.

668
00:53:28.874 --> 00:53:30.671
Mother.

669
00:53:35.154 --> 00:53:37.588
May I introduce Jack Dawson?

670
00:53:37.674 --> 00:53:39.665
Charmed. I'm sure.

671
00:53:44.594 --> 00:53:49.224
The others were gracious
about the man who saved my life

672
00:53:49.314 --> 00:53:53.227
but my mother looked at him
like an insect.

673
00:53:53.314 --> 00:53:55.509
a dangerous insect.

674
00:53:55.594 --> 00:53:57.710
which must be squashed quickly.

675
00:53:57.794 --> 00:54:02.231
Sounds like you're a good man
to have around in a sticky spot.

676
00:54:04.354 --> 00:54:07.869
Why do they always announce dinner
like a damn cavalry charge?

677
00:54:09.154 --> 00:54:11.145
Shall we go dress. Mother?

678
00:54:11.674 --> 00:54:13.665
See you at dinner. Jack.

679
00:54:14.754 --> 00:54:16.346
Uh. son?

680
00:54:16.434 --> 00:54:18.345
Son!

681
00:54:18.434 --> 00:54:20.743
Do you have any idea
what you're doing?

682
00:54:20.834 --> 00:54:22.631
Not really.

683
00:54:22.714 --> 00:54:26.104
Well. you're about
to go into the snakepit.

684
00:54:26.874 --> 00:54:29.308
What are you planning to wear?

685
00:54:31.354 --> 00:54:33.310
I figured.

686
00:54:33.394 --> 00:54:35.350
Come on.

687
00:54:36.794 --> 00:54:41.265
I was right! You and my son
are just about the same size.

688
00:54:41.354 --> 00:54:43.185
Pretty close.

689
00:54:46.514 --> 00:54:49.108
You shine up like a new penny!

690
00:54:58.434 --> 00:55:00.425
Good evening. sir.

691
00:55:49.914 --> 00:55:51.393
Good evening.

692
00:55:56.954 --> 00:55:59.184
Hello.

693
00:56:01.114 --> 00:56:05.187
There are several thousand tons
of Hockley steel

694
00:56:05.274 --> 00:56:08.744
in this very ship.

695
00:56:08.834 --> 00:56:12.793
Then we'll know who to hold
accountable if there's a problem.

696
00:56:12.874 --> 00:56:14.273
There is the Countess.

697
00:56:14.354 --> 00:56:16.310
- Hello. my dear.
- Good evening. Cal.

698
00:56:16.394 --> 00:56:19.113
So good to see you.

699
00:56:42.114 --> 00:56:46.232
I saw that in a nickelodeon once
and I always wanted to do it.

700
00:56:57.514 --> 00:56:59.470
I'll see you at dinner.

701
00:56:59.554 --> 00:57:00.623
Darling?

702
00:57:00.714 --> 00:57:03.387
Surely you remember Mr Dawson?

703
00:57:03.834 --> 00:57:05.233
Dawson?

704
00:57:05.314 --> 00:57:09.944
Well. it's amazing!
You could almost pass for a gentleman!

705
00:57:10.994 --> 00:57:12.188
Almost.

706
00:57:12.274 --> 00:57:14.071
Extraordinary!

707
00:57:24.714 --> 00:57:27.706
My dear. it's delightful to see you.

708
00:57:27.794 --> 00:57:31.150
What a remarkable voyage this is!
Mad. isn't it?

709
00:57:32.514 --> 00:57:34.789
There's the Countess of Rothes.

710
00:57:36.594 --> 00:57:41.145
And. um... that's John Jacob Astor.
the richest man on the ship.

711
00:57:41.234 --> 00:57:45.910
His little wifey. Madeleine.
is my age and in a delicate condition.

712
00:57:45.994 --> 00:57:48.554
See how she's trying to hide it?

713
00:57:48.634 --> 00:57:50.590
- Quite the scandal.
- Hmm!

714
00:57:50.674 --> 00:57:55.031
And that's Benjamin Guggenheim
and his mistress Madame Aubert.

715
00:57:55.114 --> 00:57:57.628
Mrs Guggenheim is at home
with the children.

716
00:57:57.714 --> 00:58:02.105
And over here we have Sir Cosmo
and Lucille Lady Duff-Gordon.

717
00:58:02.194 --> 00:58:04.389
She designs naughty lingerie.

718
00:58:04.474 --> 00:58:06.465
Very popular with the royals.

719
00:58:06.554 --> 00:58:09.193
Congratulations. Hockley.
She's splendid.

720
00:58:09.274 --> 00:58:11.026
Why. thank you.

721
00:58:11.114 --> 00:58:13.105
Care to escort a lady to dinner?

722
00:58:13.194 --> 00:58:14.707
Certainly.

723
00:58:15.434 --> 00:58:17.345
Sweet pea?

724
00:58:17.434 --> 00:58:18.787
Sweet pea!

725
00:58:18.874 --> 00:58:22.025
Ain't nothin' to it. Jack.
They love money.

726
00:58:22.114 --> 00:58:26.392
so just pretend like you own
a goldmine and you're in the club.

727
00:58:27.514 --> 00:58:29.311
Hey. Astor!

728
00:58:29.754 --> 00:58:32.507
Well. hello. Molly!
Nice to see you.

729
00:58:32.594 --> 00:58:35.347
JJ. Madeleine.
I'd like you to meet Jack Dawson.

730
00:58:35.434 --> 00:58:36.787
- How do you do?
- Pleasure.

731
00:58:36.874 --> 00:58:37.863
Hello. Jack.

732
00:58:37.954 --> 00:58:39.865
Are you of the Boston Dawsons?

733
00:58:39.954 --> 00:58:43.344
No... the Chippewa Falls Dawsons.
actually.

734
00:58:43.434 --> 00:58:45.106
Oh. yes...

735
00:58:47.114 --> 00:58:51.551
He must have been nervous.
but he never faltered.

736
00:58:51.634 --> 00:58:53.750
They assumed he was one of them.

737
00:58:53.834 --> 00:58:56.473
Heir to a railroad fortune. perhaps.

738
00:58:57.434 --> 00:59:01.188
New money. obviously.
but still a member of the club.

739
00:59:01.594 --> 00:59:05.109
Mother. of course.
could always be counted upon.

740
00:59:05.194 --> 00:59:08.504
Tell us of the accommodations
in steerage. Mr Dawson.

741
00:59:08.594 --> 00:59:10.391
I hear they're quite good.

742
00:59:10.474 --> 00:59:12.829
The best I've seen. ma'am.

743
00:59:12.914 --> 00:59:14.870
Hardly any rats.

744
00:59:17.634 --> 00:59:20.751
Mr Dawson is joining us
from the third class.

745
00:59:20.834 --> 00:59:23.792
He was of some assistance
to my fiancée last night.

746
00:59:23.874 --> 00:59:26.024
Mr Dawson is quite a fine artist.

747
00:59:26.114 --> 00:59:29.151
He was kind enough to show me
some of his work today.

748
00:59:29.234 --> 00:59:32.192
Rose and I differ somewhat
in our definition of fine art.

749
00:59:32.274 --> 00:59:33.992
Not to impugn your work. sir.

750
00:59:38.874 --> 00:59:41.229
She may be mine on paper

751
00:59:41.314 --> 00:59:43.953
but in the eyes of God
she belongs to Thomas Andrews.

752
00:59:44.034 --> 00:59:45.513
Are these all for me?

753
00:59:45.594 --> 00:59:48.062
Start from the outside
and work your way in.

754
00:59:48.154 --> 00:59:52.113
- He knows every rivet in her.
- Your ship is a wonder. Mr Andrews.

755
00:59:52.194 --> 00:59:53.673
Thank you. Rose.

756
00:59:56.394 --> 01:00:00.023
- How do you take your caviar. sir?
- No caviar for me. thanks.

757
01:00:00.114 --> 01:00:01.593
Never did like it much.

758
01:00:02.714 --> 01:00:05.786
And where exactly do you live.
Mr Dawson?

759
01:00:05.874 --> 01:00:08.991
Well. right now my address
is the RMS Titanic.

760
01:00:09.074 --> 01:00:11.269
After that I'm on God's good humour.

761
01:00:11.354 --> 01:00:13.584
And how is it you have means to travel?

762
01:00:13.674 --> 01:00:18.429
I work my way from place to place.
You know. tramp steamers and such.

763
01:00:18.514 --> 01:00:22.348
But I won my ticket on Titanic here
at a lucky hand at poker.

764
01:00:22.434 --> 01:00:24.072
A very lucky hand.

765
01:00:24.794 --> 01:00:26.750
All life is a game of luck.

766
01:00:26.834 --> 01:00:30.713
A real man makes his own luck. Archie.
Right. Dawson?

767
01:00:30.794 --> 01:00:32.113
Mm.

768
01:00:32.194 --> 01:00:36.870
And you find that sort of rootless
existence appealing. do you?

769
01:00:38.514 --> 01:00:40.470
Well. yes. ma'am. I do.

770
01:00:40.554 --> 01:00:44.308
I mean... Got everything I need
right here with me.

771
01:00:44.394 --> 01:00:47.033
Got air in my lungs
and a few sheets of paper.

772
01:00:47.114 --> 01:00:50.709
I love waking up in the morning
not knowing what's gonna happen

773
01:00:50.794 --> 01:00:54.833
or who I'm gonna meet.
where I'm gonna wind up.

774
01:00:54.914 --> 01:00:57.189
The other night I slept under a bridge.

775
01:00:57.274 --> 01:01:00.072
Now I'm on the grandest ship
in the world

776
01:01:00.154 --> 01:01:02.907
having champagne
with you fine people.

777
01:01:02.994 --> 01:01:07.226
I figure life's a gift
and I don't intend on wasting it.

778
01:01:07.314 --> 01:01:11.353
You never know what hand
you're gonna get dealt next.

779
01:01:11.434 --> 01:01:15.063
You learn to take life
as it comes at you.

780
01:01:15.794 --> 01:01:17.750
to make each day count.

781
01:01:17.834 --> 01:01:19.472
Well said. Jack.

782
01:01:19.554 --> 01:01:20.782
Hear. hear!

783
01:01:20.874 --> 01:01:23.308
To making it count.

784
01:01:24.754 --> 01:01:26.745
To making it count.

785
01:01:26.834 --> 01:01:27.823
Bravo!

786
01:01:34.794 --> 01:01:39.390
Mr Brown had no idea
I'd hidden the money in the stove!

787
01:01:39.474 --> 01:01:43.353
So he comes home drunk as a pig
and he lights a fire!

788
01:01:46.034 --> 01:01:48.753
Next it'll be brandies
in the smoking room.

789
01:01:50.634 --> 01:01:52.750
Join me in a brandy. gentlemen?

790
01:01:52.834 --> 01:01:55.302
Now they retreat
into a cloud of smoke

791
01:01:55.394 --> 01:01:58.864
and congratulate each other
on being masters of the universe.

792
01:01:58.954 --> 01:02:00.990
Ladies. thank you for your company.

793
01:02:01.074 --> 01:02:04.749
- May I escort you to the cabin?
- No. I'll stay here.

794
01:02:04.834 --> 01:02:06.506
Here you go. Molly.

795
01:02:07.514 --> 01:02:09.709
Joining us. Dawson?

796
01:02:09.794 --> 01:02:12.069
Don't want to stay with the women.
do you?

797
01:02:12.154 --> 01:02:14.827
No. thanks.
I've gotta be heading back.

798
01:02:14.914 --> 01:02:19.669
Probably best. It'll be all business
and politics. Wouldn't interest you.

799
01:02:20.754 --> 01:02:23.222
But. Dawson... Good of you to come.

800
01:02:27.874 --> 01:02:29.830
Jack. must you go?

801
01:02:29.914 --> 01:02:32.348
Time for me to row
with the other slaves.

802
01:02:35.514 --> 01:02:37.869
Good night. Rose.

803
01:03:15.674 --> 01:03:18.234
So you wanna go to a real party?

804
01:03:27.194 --> 01:03:29.071
Is okay I put my hand here?

805
01:03:29.154 --> 01:03:30.143
Okay!

806
01:03:43.194 --> 01:03:45.071
Talla frikken svenska?

807
01:03:45.154 --> 01:03:46.223
What?

808
01:03:48.194 --> 01:03:50.185
I can't understand you.

809
01:04:14.914 --> 01:04:16.347
Hey...!

810
01:04:16.434 --> 01:04:18.390
Bravo! Bravo!

811
01:04:18.474 --> 01:04:20.624
Come on. guys. let's go! Ho!

812
01:04:20.714 --> 01:04:23.831
I'm gonna dance with her now.
all right?

813
01:04:23.914 --> 01:04:24.949
Come on.

814
01:04:25.034 --> 01:04:26.467
Come on!

815
01:04:26.554 --> 01:04:27.543
Come with me.

816
01:04:27.634 --> 01:04:29.511
Jack... Jack. wait!

817
01:04:31.114 --> 01:04:32.672
I can't do this.

818
01:04:32.754 --> 01:04:34.745
We have to get a bit closer.

819
01:04:34.834 --> 01:04:36.426
Like this.

820
01:04:38.594 --> 01:04:40.903
You're still my best girl. Cora.

821
01:04:43.434 --> 01:04:47.427
- I don't know the steps.
- Neither do I. Just go with it.

822
01:04:47.514 --> 01:04:49.266
Don't think.

823
01:05:07.194 --> 01:05:09.992
Wait. Jack! Wait! Stop. Jack!

824
01:05:19.514 --> 01:05:20.549
Wait!

825
01:05:58.794 --> 01:06:00.068
Yeah!

826
01:06:00.154 --> 01:06:01.872
Jack... No!

827
01:06:01.954 --> 01:06:04.263
Whaaa...

828
01:06:07.194 --> 01:06:11.187
...jurisdiction of the Sherman Act.
so my lawyers will argue.

829
01:06:11.274 --> 01:06:14.710
That's what Rockefeller said.
but the court is not swallowing it.

830
01:06:33.914 --> 01:06:35.347
What?

831
01:06:35.434 --> 01:06:38.665
You think a first-class girl can't drink?

832
01:06:38.754 --> 01:06:40.710
Get outta here!

833
01:06:40.794 --> 01:06:42.864
You all right?

834
01:06:46.554 --> 01:06:48.749
Two out of three. two out of three.

835
01:06:48.834 --> 01:06:49.983
So...

836
01:06:51.274 --> 01:06:53.549
You think you're big. tough men?

837
01:06:53.634 --> 01:06:55.670
Let's see you do this.

838
01:06:57.034 --> 01:06:59.229
Hold this for me. Jack.

839
01:06:59.314 --> 01:07:01.111
Hold it up.

840
01:07:14.474 --> 01:07:15.463
Ow!

841
01:07:16.434 --> 01:07:18.390
Jesus. Mary and Joseph!

842
01:07:18.474 --> 01:07:21.546
- You all right?
- I haven't done that in years!

843
01:07:29.274 --> 01:07:32.072
Go see Maggie. lads. Let's go!

844
01:07:56.714 --> 01:07:58.705
Coffee. sir?

845
01:08:06.114 --> 01:08:09.311
I had hoped you would
come to me last night.

846
01:08:11.714 --> 01:08:13.864
I was tired.

847
01:08:13.954 --> 01:08:17.913
Your exertions below decks
were no doubt exhausting.

848
01:08:20.114 --> 01:08:25.234
I see you had that undertaker
of a manservant follow me. How typical.

849
01:08:25.314 --> 01:08:29.785
You will never behave like that again.
Rose. Do you understand?

850
01:08:29.914 --> 01:08:34.066
I'm not a foreman in one of your mills
that you can command.

851
01:08:34.154 --> 01:08:36.793
I'm your fiancée.

852
01:08:38.314 --> 01:08:40.270
My fiancée? My fiancée?!

853
01:08:40.354 --> 01:08:43.585
Yes. you are. and my wife!

854
01:08:43.674 --> 01:08:48.225
M wife in practice if not yet by law.
so you will honour me.

855
01:08:48.314 --> 01:08:51.545
You will honour me
the way a wife is required to.

856
01:08:51.634 --> 01:08:53.465
I will not be made a fool of.

857
01:08:53.554 --> 01:08:55.784
Is this in any way unclear?

858
01:08:56.834 --> 01:08:58.028
No.

859
01:08:58.114 --> 01:08:59.467
Good.

860
01:08:59.554 --> 01:09:01.510
Excuse me.

861
01:09:06.114 --> 01:09:07.945
Miss Rose!

862
01:09:08.034 --> 01:09:11.629
- We had a little... accident.
- That's all right. Miss Rose.

863
01:09:11.714 --> 01:09:14.467
I'm sorry. Trudy. Let me help you.

864
01:09:14.554 --> 01:09:16.545
It's all right. miss.

865
01:09:21.914 --> 01:09:23.905
It's all right. miss.

866
01:09:28.754 --> 01:09:29.823
Tea. Trudy.

867
01:09:29.954 --> 01:09:31.910
Yes. ma'am.

868
01:09:47.354 --> 01:09:51.393
You're not to see that boy again.
Do you understand me?

869
01:09:51.474 --> 01:09:54.068
Rose. I forbid it.

870
01:09:54.154 --> 01:09:57.863
Oh. stop it. Mother.
You'll give yourself a nosebleed.

871
01:09:57.994 --> 01:09:59.825
This is not a game.

872
01:09:59.914 --> 01:10:03.668
Our situation is precarious.
You know the money's gone.

873
01:10:03.754 --> 01:10:06.188
Of course I know it's gone.

874
01:10:06.314 --> 01:10:08.270
You remind me every day.

875
01:10:08.354 --> 01:10:11.983
Your father left us nothing
but a legacy of bad debts

876
01:10:12.074 --> 01:10:13.587
hidden by a good name.

877
01:10:13.674 --> 01:10:16.632
That name is the only card
we have to play.

878
01:10:16.714 --> 01:10:18.705
I don't understand you.

879
01:10:19.194 --> 01:10:21.583
It is a fine match with Hockley.

880
01:10:21.674 --> 01:10:23.630
It will ensure our survival.

881
01:10:23.714 --> 01:10:26.182
How can you put this on my shoulders?

882
01:10:26.274 --> 01:10:27.912
Why are you being so selfish?

883
01:10:27.994 --> 01:10:30.383
I'm being selfish?

884
01:10:33.754 --> 01:10:37.190
Do you want to see me
working as a seamstress?

885
01:10:38.274 --> 01:10:40.583
Is that what you want?

886
01:10:42.674 --> 01:10:45.586
To see our fine things
sold at auction?

887
01:10:45.674 --> 01:10:48.586
Our memories scattered to the winds!

888
01:10:59.354 --> 01:11:01.868
It's so unfair.

889
01:11:01.954 --> 01:11:03.945
Of course it's unfair.

890
01:11:05.154 --> 01:11:07.145
We're women.

891
01:11:08.954 --> 01:11:11.343
Our choices are never easy.

892
01:11:17.754 --> 01:11:19.665
Hmm?

893
01:11:31.634 --> 01:11:35.627
Protect them by thy guardian hand...

894
01:11:35.714 --> 01:11:41.027
From every peril on the land...

895
01:11:42.314 --> 01:11:46.626
O spirit. whom the father sent...

896
01:11:46.714 --> 01:11:50.593
To spread across the firmament...

897
01:11:50.674 --> 01:11:55.145
O wind of heaven. by thy might...

898
01:11:55.434 --> 01:12:00.224
Save all who dare the eagle's flight...

899
01:12:00.314 --> 01:12:04.353
And keep them by thy watchful...

900
01:12:06.314 --> 01:12:08.066
Hello. Mr Andrews.

901
01:12:08.154 --> 01:12:09.951
Hello. Jack.

902
01:12:17.394 --> 01:12:20.431
- Sir...
- I just need to talk to somebody...

903
01:12:20.514 --> 01:12:22.869
You're not supposed to be in here.

904
01:12:22.954 --> 01:12:24.910
Fire and foe...

905
01:12:24.994 --> 01:12:26.347
Protect them...

906
01:12:26.434 --> 01:12:28.948
- You don't remember me?
- No. I don't.

907
01:12:29.034 --> 01:12:31.707
- You'll have to turn around.
- He'll tell you.

908
01:12:31.794 --> 01:12:33.068
I just...

909
01:12:33.154 --> 01:12:35.748
Mr Hockley and Mrs DeWitt Bukater

910
01:12:35.834 --> 01:12:39.543
continue to be appreciative
of your assistance.

911
01:12:39.634 --> 01:12:42.865
They asked me to give you this
in gratitude.

912
01:12:42.954 --> 01:12:44.546
I don't want your money...

913
01:12:44.634 --> 01:12:50.425
You hold a third-class ticket.
Your presence here is no longer appropriate.

914
01:12:50.514 --> 01:12:52.470
Please. I just wanna speak to Rose...

915
01:12:52.554 --> 01:12:56.183
Gentlemen. please see that Mr Dawson
gets back to where he belongs

916
01:12:56.314 --> 01:12:58.305
and that he stays there.

917
01:12:58.394 --> 01:12:59.383
Yes. sir.

918
01:12:59.434 --> 01:13:01.425
Come along. you.

919
01:13:03.034 --> 01:13:06.185
O hear us when we cry to Thee...

920
01:13:06.354 --> 01:13:11.747
For those in peril on the sea...

921
01:13:11.794 --> 01:13:15.628
- Why two steering wheels?
- We only use this near shore.

922
01:13:15.674 --> 01:13:19.349
Sir. another ice warning.
This one's from the Noordam.

923
01:13:19.394 --> 01:13:21.464
Thank you. Sparks.

924
01:13:22.314 --> 01:13:26.023
Oh. not to worry.
Quite normal for this time of year.

925
01:13:26.074 --> 01:13:30.784
In fact. we're speeding up.
I've just ordered the last boilers lit.

926
01:13:34.394 --> 01:13:37.352
Okay. son. wind it up tight
like I showed you.

927
01:13:37.394 --> 01:13:39.385
Okay. let it go.

928
01:13:41.994 --> 01:13:43.871
- Was good. wasn't it?
- Quite nice.

929
01:13:43.914 --> 01:13:45.825
That's excellent. son.

930
01:13:49.354 --> 01:13:52.630
Mr Andrews. forgive me...

931
01:13:53.674 --> 01:13:55.665
I did the sum in my head...

932
01:13:55.714 --> 01:14:00.105
With the number of lifeboats
times the capacity you mentioned

933
01:14:00.154 --> 01:14:03.191
it seems there are not enough
for everyone.

934
01:14:03.234 --> 01:14:05.225
About half. actually.

935
01:14:05.314 --> 01:14:07.828
Rose. you miss nothing. do you?

936
01:14:07.874 --> 01:14:10.672
In fact.
I put in these new type davits

937
01:14:10.714 --> 01:14:13.467
which can take an extra row of boats.

938
01:14:13.514 --> 01:14:17.712
But it was thought by some
that the deck would look too cluttered

939
01:14:17.754 --> 01:14:20.712
so I was overruled.

940
01:14:20.754 --> 01:14:23.871
Waste of deck space
on an unsinkable ship.

941
01:14:23.914 --> 01:14:25.745
Sleep soundly. young Rose.

942
01:14:25.794 --> 01:14:28.911
I have built you a good ship.
strong and true.

943
01:14:28.954 --> 01:14:31.104
She is all the lifeboat you need.

944
01:14:31.154 --> 01:14:33.145
Just keep heading aft.

945
01:14:33.194 --> 01:14:34.991
Come on.

946
01:14:38.514 --> 01:14:40.869
Jack. this is impossible.

947
01:14:40.914 --> 01:14:42.905
I can't see you.

948
01:14:42.954 --> 01:14:45.946
- I need to talk to you.
- No. Jack. no.

949
01:14:46.554 --> 01:14:48.545
Jack. I'm engaged.

950
01:14:50.194 --> 01:14:52.185
I'm marrying Cal.

951
01:14:52.234 --> 01:14:53.986
I love Cal.

952
01:14:56.274 --> 01:14:59.266
Rose... you're no picnic.

953
01:15:00.114 --> 01:15:02.753
You're a spoiled little brat. even.

954
01:15:02.794 --> 01:15:08.073
But you're the most amazingly
astounding. wonderful girl.

955
01:15:08.114 --> 01:15:09.513
woman.

956
01:15:09.554 --> 01:15:12.273
- that I've ever known. and...
- Jack...

957
01:15:12.314 --> 01:15:14.305
Let me try and get this out.

958
01:15:14.354 --> 01:15:16.106
You're ama...

959
01:15:17.314 --> 01:15:20.670
I'm not an idiot.
I know how the world works.

960
01:15:20.714 --> 01:15:25.310
I've got ten bucks in my pocket
and I have nothing to offer you.

961
01:15:25.354 --> 01:15:27.345
I understand.

962
01:15:27.634 --> 01:15:29.625
But I'm too involved now.

963
01:15:29.674 --> 01:15:31.665
You jump. I jump. remember?

964
01:15:31.714 --> 01:15:37.027
I can't turn away without knowing
you'll be all right. That's all I want.

965
01:15:38.794 --> 01:15:40.785
Well. I'm fine.

966
01:15:41.314 --> 01:15:44.033
I'll be fine... Really.

967
01:15:44.074 --> 01:15:45.871
Really?

968
01:15:47.994 --> 01:15:49.985
I don't think so.

969
01:15:50.034 --> 01:15:54.710
They've got you trapped. Rose.
and you'll die if you don't break free.

970
01:15:54.754 --> 01:15:57.871
Maybe not right away
because you're strong. but

971
01:15:57.914 --> 01:16:01.065
that fire that I love about you. Rose.

972
01:16:01.114 --> 01:16:03.708
that fire is gonna burn out.

973
01:16:07.314 --> 01:16:10.192
It's not up to you to save me. Jack.

974
01:16:12.514 --> 01:16:14.505
You're right.

975
01:16:14.834 --> 01:16:17.302
Only you can do that.

976
01:16:22.034 --> 01:16:24.025
I'm going back.

977
01:16:24.074 --> 01:16:26.065
Leave me alone.

978
01:16:35.674 --> 01:16:39.872
Tell Lucille about the disaster
you had with the stationer's.

979
01:16:39.914 --> 01:16:42.667
The invitations
had to be sent back twice.

980
01:16:42.714 --> 01:16:44.113
Oh. my dear!

981
01:16:44.154 --> 01:16:48.067
And the dreadful bridesmaids' gowns
- what an odyssey that has been!

982
01:16:48.114 --> 01:16:50.992
Rose decided she wanted lavender.

983
01:16:51.034 --> 01:16:54.106
She knows I detest the colour.
so she did it to spite me.

984
01:16:54.154 --> 01:16:56.224
If only you'd come to me sooner.

985
01:16:56.274 --> 01:16:59.152
Ruth saw some of my designs
in "La Mode Illustree".

986
01:16:59.194 --> 01:17:02.345
They were for the Duchess
of Marlborough's youngest.

987
01:17:02.394 --> 01:17:05.591
They were quite charming.
But I think you'll agree. my dear.

988
01:17:05.634 --> 01:17:09.786
together we've created something
of a phoenix from the ashes!

989
01:17:21.914 --> 01:17:23.905
Hello. Jack.

990
01:17:29.154 --> 01:17:31.145
I changed my mind.

991
01:17:36.074 --> 01:17:39.510
- They said you might be...
- Shh...

992
01:17:40.154 --> 01:17:42.145
Give me your hand.

993
01:17:49.274 --> 01:17:52.027
Now close your eyes.

994
01:17:52.074 --> 01:17:54.065
Go on.

995
01:17:56.394 --> 01:17:58.385
Step up.

996
01:18:00.874 --> 01:18:03.024
Now hold on to the railing.

997
01:18:03.074 --> 01:18:05.952
- Keep your eyes closed. Don't peek.
- I'm not.

998
01:18:07.474 --> 01:18:09.465
Step up onto the rail.

999
01:18:13.074 --> 01:18:15.065
Hold on... Hold on.

1000
01:18:15.114 --> 01:18:17.264
Keep your eyes closed.

1001
01:18:17.314 --> 01:18:19.305
Do you trust me?

1002
01:18:19.354 --> 01:18:21.265
I trust you.

1003
01:18:30.074 --> 01:18:31.632
All right...

1004
01:18:31.674 --> 01:18:33.665
Open your eyes.

1005
01:18:39.554 --> 01:18:41.146
I'm flying!

1006
01:18:41.194 --> 01:18:42.832
Jack!

1007
01:19:06.194 --> 01:19:10.187
Come. Josephine. on my flying machine...

1008
01:19:10.234 --> 01:19:14.944
Going up. she goes. up. she goes...

1009
01:19:58.874 --> 01:20:02.833
That was the last time
Titanic ever saw daylight.

1010
01:20:02.874 --> 01:20:06.389
So we're up to dusk
the night of the sinking.

1011
01:20:06.434 --> 01:20:08.425
Six hours to go.

1012
01:20:08.474 --> 01:20:13.423
Smith's standing there. the iceberg
warning in his fucking hand.

1013
01:20:13.474 --> 01:20:16.068
and he's ordering more speed.

1014
01:20:16.114 --> 01:20:19.550
26 years of experience
working against him.

1015
01:20:19.594 --> 01:20:24.270
He figures anything big enough
to sink the ship they'll see in time to turn.

1016
01:20:24.314 --> 01:20:29.229
But the ship's too big with too small
a rudder. Doesn't corner worth a damn.

1017
01:20:29.274 --> 01:20:31.390
Everything he knows is wrong.

1018
01:20:42.674 --> 01:20:45.666
It's quite proper. I assure you!

1019
01:20:45.714 --> 01:20:47.705
This is the sitting room.

1020
01:20:48.714 --> 01:20:50.989
- Will this light do?
- What?

1021
01:20:51.034 --> 01:20:53.150
Don't artists need good light?

1022
01:20:53.234 --> 01:20:56.271
I am not used to working in such

1023
01:20:56.314 --> 01:20:57.872
horrible conditions.

1024
01:20:58.554 --> 01:21:00.351
Monet!

1025
01:21:00.714 --> 01:21:03.592
- Do you know his work?
- Of course!

1026
01:21:03.674 --> 01:21:05.790
Look at his use of colour here!

1027
01:21:05.834 --> 01:21:07.745
I know. it's extraordinary.

1028
01:21:09.594 --> 01:21:13.507
Cal insists on carting
this hideous thing everywhere.

1029
01:21:13.994 --> 01:21:16.872
Should we be expecting him
any time soon?

1030
01:21:17.194 --> 01:21:20.345
Not as long as the cigars
and brandy hold out.

1031
01:21:22.474 --> 01:21:24.465
That's nice!

1032
01:21:24.514 --> 01:21:26.869
What is it? A sapphire?

1033
01:21:26.914 --> 01:21:28.791
A diamond.

1034
01:21:28.834 --> 01:21:30.552
A very rare diamond.

1035
01:21:32.554 --> 01:21:36.388
Jack. I want you to draw me
like one of your French girls

1036
01:21:37.394 --> 01:21:39.350
wearing this.

1037
01:21:39.394 --> 01:21:40.543
All right.

1038
01:21:42.154 --> 01:21:44.145
Wearing only this.

1039
01:22:18.114 --> 01:22:19.866
The last thing I need

1040
01:22:19.954 --> 01:22:24.106
is another picture of me
looking like a porcelain doll.

1041
01:22:25.394 --> 01:22:27.430
As a paying customer

1042
01:22:29.314 --> 01:22:31.748
I expect to get what I want.

1043
01:22:48.394 --> 01:22:50.954
Over on the bed... the couch.

1044
01:22:58.914 --> 01:23:00.632
Go... lie down.

1045
01:23:03.394 --> 01:23:05.350
Tell me when it looks right.

1046
01:23:05.394 --> 01:23:07.988
Put your arm back the way it was.

1047
01:23:08.034 --> 01:23:09.467
Right.

1048
01:23:09.514 --> 01:23:13.223
Put that other arm up...
That hand right by your face.

1049
01:23:13.274 --> 01:23:15.265
Right.

1050
01:23:16.594 --> 01:23:18.824
Now. head down...

1051
01:23:20.994 --> 01:23:22.985
Eyes to me. Keep them on me.

1052
01:23:23.794 --> 01:23:25.785
And try to stay still.

1053
01:23:44.314 --> 01:23:45.713
So serious!

1054
01:24:25.674 --> 01:24:29.986
I believe you are blushing.
Mr Big Artiste.

1055
01:24:33.114 --> 01:24:36.629
I can't imagine
Monsieur Monet blushing.

1056
01:24:36.674 --> 01:24:39.029
He does landscapes.

1057
01:24:39.074 --> 01:24:42.146
- Just relax your face.
- Sorry.

1058
01:24:42.194 --> 01:24:44.185
No laughing.

1059
01:25:13.114 --> 01:25:16.106
My heart was pounding the whole time.

1060
01:25:16.394 --> 01:25:20.182
It was the most erotic moment of my life.

1061
01:25:23.794 --> 01:25:26.228
Up until then. at least.

1062
01:25:26.274 --> 01:25:28.026
So what happened next?

1063
01:25:28.074 --> 01:25:31.703
You mean... did we do it?

1064
01:25:33.754 --> 01:25:36.109
Sorry to disappoint you. Mr Bodine.

1065
01:25:36.154 --> 01:25:38.509
Jack was very professional.

1066
01:25:46.794 --> 01:25:48.591
Thank you.

1067
01:25:55.794 --> 01:25:57.785
What are you doing?

1068
01:25:57.834 --> 01:26:01.304
Will you put this back
in the safe for me?

1069
01:26:11.514 --> 01:26:13.505
Would you excuse me?

1070
01:26:14.514 --> 01:26:17.426
None of the stewards have seen her.

1071
01:26:17.474 --> 01:26:19.465
This is absurd.

1072
01:26:19.514 --> 01:26:23.223
It's a ship. There's only
so many places she could be.

1073
01:26:23.274 --> 01:26:25.151
Lovejoy. find her.

1074
01:26:41.874 --> 01:26:43.865
- Clear.
- Yes.

1075
01:26:44.514 --> 01:26:47.665
I don't think I've ever seen
such a flat calm.

1076
01:26:47.714 --> 01:26:49.386
Like a millpond.

1077
01:26:49.434 --> 01:26:51.425
Not a breath of wind.

1078
01:26:53.074 --> 01:26:55.793
It will make the bergs harder to see

1079
01:26:56.114 --> 01:26:58.753
with no breaking water at the base.

1080
01:27:08.674 --> 01:27:10.505
Well. I'm off.

1081
01:27:10.554 --> 01:27:13.751
Maintain speed and heading.
Mr Lightoller.

1082
01:27:13.794 --> 01:27:15.227
Yes. sir.

1083
01:27:25.434 --> 01:27:27.425
It's getting cold.

1084
01:27:27.474 --> 01:27:29.032
You look nice.

1085
01:27:29.074 --> 01:27:30.632
Miss Rose?

1086
01:27:30.674 --> 01:27:32.073
My drawings!

1087
01:28:01.194 --> 01:28:02.593
Wait!

1088
01:28:02.634 --> 01:28:04.352
Wait. wait. wait!

1089
01:28:04.394 --> 01:28:05.429
Go. go!

1090
01:28:05.474 --> 01:28:06.668
Down. down!

1091
01:28:13.474 --> 01:28:14.463
Bye!

1092
01:28:21.594 --> 01:28:22.583
Sorry!

1093
01:28:39.274 --> 01:28:41.993
Pretty tough for a valet. this fellow.

1094
01:28:42.034 --> 01:28:44.787
- Seems more like a cop.
- I think he was.

1095
01:28:44.834 --> 01:28:47.109
Oh. shit!

1096
01:28:51.634 --> 01:28:53.625
No. over here!

1097
01:28:53.674 --> 01:28:55.232
Quick!

1098
01:29:01.114 --> 01:29:02.706
Now what!

1099
01:29:02.754 --> 01:29:04.073
What!

1100
01:29:10.714 --> 01:29:13.274
What are you two doing here?

1101
01:29:13.314 --> 01:29:15.828
You shouldn't be here!
It's dangerous!

1102
01:29:19.514 --> 01:29:21.106
Carry on!

1103
01:29:21.154 --> 01:29:25.147
Don't mind us! You're doing a greatjob!
Keep up the good work!

1104
01:29:40.674 --> 01:29:43.063
Look what we have here. huh?

1105
01:30:00.074 --> 01:30:01.871
Thank you.

1106
01:30:12.434 --> 01:30:14.425
Where to. miss?

1107
01:30:15.554 --> 01:30:17.545
To the stars.

1108
01:30:35.234 --> 01:30:37.225
Are you nervous?

1109
01:30:39.434 --> 01:30:41.425
No.

1110
01:30:56.514 --> 01:30:58.903
Put your hands on me. Jack.

1111
01:31:20.394 --> 01:31:22.783
God. it's bloody cold.

1112
01:31:22.834 --> 01:31:26.588
You know. I can smell ice.
you know... when it's near.

1113
01:31:28.114 --> 01:31:29.433
Bollocks.

1114
01:31:29.474 --> 01:31:31.305
But I can. all right?

1115
01:31:31.354 --> 01:31:33.868
Did you ever find those binoculars?

1116
01:31:33.914 --> 01:31:36.474
Haven't seen them since Southampton.

1117
01:31:36.514 --> 01:31:39.074
Well. I'll be on my rounds. Cheerio.

1118
01:32:09.394 --> 01:32:11.385
You're trembling.

1119
01:32:12.674 --> 01:32:15.234
Don't worry. I'll be all right.

1120
01:32:35.274 --> 01:32:37.185
They ran down there.

1121
01:32:37.234 --> 01:32:38.633
Right.

1122
01:32:47.554 --> 01:32:49.545
Anything missing?

1123
01:33:13.034 --> 01:33:15.025
I've got a better idea.

1124
01:33:26.594 --> 01:33:28.073
Gotcha!

1125
01:33:38.034 --> 01:33:40.150
Did you see those guys' faces?

1126
01:33:40.554 --> 01:33:42.545
Did you see the...?

1127
01:33:48.274 --> 01:33:50.708
When the ship docks

1128
01:33:50.754 --> 01:33:52.745
I'm getting off with you.

1129
01:33:52.794 --> 01:33:54.989
This is crazy.

1130
01:33:55.034 --> 01:33:57.423
I know! It doesn't make any sense.

1131
01:33:58.834 --> 01:34:00.825
That's why I trust it.

1132
01:34:09.074 --> 01:34:12.146
Oh. yes... Here. look at this.

1133
01:34:12.194 --> 01:34:16.506
- Look at that. would ya?
- They're a bit warmer than we are.

1134
01:34:16.554 --> 01:34:21.867
Well. if that's what it takes for us
to get warm. I'd rather not!

1135
01:34:32.274 --> 01:34:34.230
Bugger me!

1136
01:34:38.914 --> 01:34:40.825
Pick up. you bastards!

1137
01:34:43.474 --> 01:34:46.625
- Is there anyone there?!
- Yes. what do you see?

1138
01:34:46.674 --> 01:34:48.232
Iceberg! Right ahead!

1139
01:34:48.314 --> 01:34:50.032
Thank you.

1140
01:34:50.794 --> 01:34:52.625
Iceberg! Right ahead!

1141
01:34:52.674 --> 01:34:54.869
Hard to starboard!

1142
01:35:01.114 --> 01:35:03.582
Turn! Turn! Steady!

1143
01:35:08.034 --> 01:35:09.592
Full astern!

1144
01:35:11.274 --> 01:35:12.673
Hard over!

1145
01:35:12.714 --> 01:35:14.705
Helm's hard over. sir!

1146
01:35:18.034 --> 01:35:19.752
Go. lads! Go!

1147
01:35:25.794 --> 01:35:27.944
Shut all the dampers!

1148
01:35:27.994 --> 01:35:29.712
Shut them!

1149
01:35:33.514 --> 01:35:34.947
Hold it!

1150
01:35:36.034 --> 01:35:37.183
Hold it!

1151
01:35:38.554 --> 01:35:41.387
Now! Engage the reversing engine!

1152
01:36:07.314 --> 01:36:09.589
Why aren't they turning?!

1153
01:36:09.634 --> 01:36:11.147
Is it hard over?!

1154
01:36:11.194 --> 01:36:13.503
It is. yes. sir. hard over!

1155
01:36:16.474 --> 01:36:20.149
Come on... come on... come on...

1156
01:36:20.194 --> 01:36:21.627
Turn...

1157
01:36:31.474 --> 01:36:33.146
Yes...

1158
01:36:37.674 --> 01:36:39.665
It's going to hit!

1159
01:36:50.394 --> 01:36:51.952
Jesus Christ!

1160
01:37:11.234 --> 01:37:12.986
Jesus...

1161
01:37:13.034 --> 01:37:14.183
Hard to port!

1162
01:37:14.234 --> 01:37:15.713
Hard to port!

1163
01:37:25.074 --> 01:37:26.871
Get back!

1164
01:37:54.714 --> 01:37:58.024
Come on. let's go!
They're closing the doors!

1165
01:37:58.074 --> 01:37:59.632
Get out!

1166
01:38:00.674 --> 01:38:02.665
Get out! Get out!

1167
01:38:05.634 --> 01:38:06.987
Get out the door!

1168
01:38:07.034 --> 01:38:08.149
Go on!

1169
01:38:08.194 --> 01:38:09.946
Come on. lads!

1170
01:38:09.994 --> 01:38:11.222
Go. lads. go!

1171
01:38:18.234 --> 01:38:19.110
Get out!

1172
01:38:38.234 --> 01:38:39.553
Oh. my God...

1173
01:38:39.594 --> 01:38:42.188
That was a close shave. weren't it?

1174
01:38:42.234 --> 01:38:45.431
Smell ice. can ya? Bleedin' Christ!

1175
01:38:48.914 --> 01:38:51.986
Note the time and enter it in the log.

1176
01:38:57.034 --> 01:38:59.184
What was that. Mr Murdoch?

1177
01:38:59.234 --> 01:39:01.350
An iceberg. sir.

1178
01:39:01.394 --> 01:39:05.023
I put her hard to starboard
and ran the engines full astern

1179
01:39:05.074 --> 01:39:08.510
but it was too close.
I tried to port round it. but she hit and...

1180
01:39:08.554 --> 01:39:12.149
- Close the watertight doors.
- Doors are closed. sir.

1181
01:39:14.474 --> 01:39:16.749
All stop.

1182
01:39:22.914 --> 01:39:25.712
Find the carpenter.
Get him to sound the ship.

1183
01:39:25.754 --> 01:39:26.743
Yes. sir!

1184
01:39:30.274 --> 01:39:32.947
Porca puttana!

1185
01:39:32.994 --> 01:39:34.985
Che cazzo e?

1186
01:39:36.714 --> 01:39:39.433
Come on.
let's get the hell out of here!

1187
01:39:39.474 --> 01:39:41.192
Come on. hurry up!

1188
01:39:45.714 --> 01:39:48.865
Why have the engines stopped?
I felt a shudder.

1189
01:39:48.914 --> 01:39:53.271
I shouldn't worry. madam.
We've likely thrown a propeller blade.

1190
01:39:53.314 --> 01:39:56.112
- May I bring you anything?
- No. thank you.

1191
01:40:00.754 --> 01:40:05.145
- Did you see anything?
- I don't see anything now. do you?

1192
01:40:06.114 --> 01:40:10.312
If this is the direction the rats are going.
that's good enough for me.

1193
01:40:11.954 --> 01:40:15.390
Please. sir. please...
everything's under control.

1194
01:40:16.594 --> 01:40:19.154
- You there.
- Sir. there is no emergency.

1195
01:40:19.194 --> 01:40:21.549
- I have been robbed.
- Get the master-at-arms.

1196
01:40:21.594 --> 01:40:24.233
- Now. you moron!
- Yes. sir.

1197
01:40:28.154 --> 01:40:30.349
Hey. you're gonna miss the fun.

1198
01:40:30.394 --> 01:40:34.706
- Did you see what happened?
- No. Apparently. it hit over there.

1199
01:40:36.194 --> 01:40:39.072
It's flooded eight feet
and the mail hold is worse.

1200
01:40:39.114 --> 01:40:42.186
- Can you shore up?
- Not unless the pumps get ahead.

1201
01:40:42.234 --> 01:40:45.909
- Have you seen the mail-hold damage?
- No. she's already underwater.

1202
01:40:45.954 --> 01:40:47.945
This is bad.

1203
01:40:48.114 --> 01:40:50.184
We should tell Mother and Cal.

1204
01:40:52.353 --> 01:40:54.548
I think they're very good. sir.

1205
01:40:55.513 --> 01:40:59.711
Don't touch anything.
I want the entire room photographed.

1206
01:40:59.753 --> 01:41:02.028
Just keep holding my hand.

1207
01:41:04.153 --> 01:41:06.542
We've been looking for you. miss.

1208
01:41:10.113 --> 01:41:12.308
Well. here we go.

1209
01:41:16.953 --> 01:41:19.308
Something serious has happened.

1210
01:41:20.713 --> 01:41:22.590
Yes. it has.

1211
01:41:22.633 --> 01:41:27.024
Indeed. Two things dear to me
have disappeared this evening.

1212
01:41:27.073 --> 01:41:31.828
Now that one is back. I've an idea
where to find the other. Search him.

1213
01:41:31.873 --> 01:41:34.626
- Take your coat off. sir.
- Now what?

1214
01:41:34.673 --> 01:41:36.948
Cal. we're in the middle
of an emergency.

1215
01:41:36.993 --> 01:41:38.665
What's going on?

1216
01:41:38.713 --> 01:41:40.465
- Is this it?
- That's it.

1217
01:41:40.513 --> 01:41:42.743
This is horseshit!

1218
01:41:42.793 --> 01:41:44.863
Don't you believe it. Rose!

1219
01:41:44.913 --> 01:41:49.225
- He couldn't have.
- Of course he could.

1220
01:41:49.273 --> 01:41:51.628
But I was with him the whole time.

1221
01:41:51.673 --> 01:41:56.189
Perhaps he did it while you were
putting your clothes back on. dear.

1222
01:41:56.233 --> 01:41:58.383
Rose. they put it in my pocket.

1223
01:41:58.433 --> 01:41:59.468
Shut up.

1224
01:41:59.513 --> 01:42:01.390
It isn't even your pocket.

1225
01:42:01.433 --> 01:42:03.025
Property of AL Ryerson.

1226
01:42:07.073 --> 01:42:11.191
- That was reported stolen.
- I borrowed it. I was gonna return it.

1227
01:42:11.233 --> 01:42:15.226
- We have an honest thief. do we?
- You know I didn't do this. Rose.

1228
01:42:15.273 --> 01:42:18.106
Don't you believe them. Rose.

1229
01:42:18.153 --> 01:42:21.225
You know I didn't do it.
You know I didn't do it. Rose!

1230
01:42:21.273 --> 01:42:23.662
Come on. son. There's a good lad.

1231
01:42:23.713 --> 01:42:24.702
Come on.

1232
01:42:24.753 --> 01:42:27.028
You know I didn't do it!
You know me!

1233
01:42:28.673 --> 01:42:31.665
Most unfortunate. Captain.

1234
01:42:33.953 --> 01:42:37.343
Water... 14 feet above the keel
in 10 minutes

1235
01:42:37.753 --> 01:42:41.143
in the forepeak. in all three holds
and in boiler room six.

1236
01:42:41.193 --> 01:42:42.546
That's right. sir.

1237
01:42:42.593 --> 01:42:47.109
- When can we get under way. damn it!
- That's five compartments!

1238
01:42:47.233 --> 01:42:52.307
She can stay afloat with the first four
compartments breached. but not five.

1239
01:42:52.353 --> 01:42:53.786
Not five.

1240
01:42:53.833 --> 01:42:55.869
As she goes down by the head

1241
01:42:55.913 --> 01:43:00.065
the water will spill over
the bulkheads. from one to the next.

1242
01:43:00.113 --> 01:43:02.866
Back and back.
There's no stopping it.

1243
01:43:02.913 --> 01:43:03.868
The pumps...

1244
01:43:03.913 --> 01:43:07.667
The pumps buy you time.
but minutes only.

1245
01:43:07.713 --> 01:43:10.466
From this moment. no matter what we do.

1246
01:43:10.513 --> 01:43:13.107
Titanic will founder.

1247
01:43:15.353 --> 01:43:17.344
But this ship can't sink.

1248
01:43:17.393 --> 01:43:20.305
She's made of iron. sir.
I assure you she can.

1249
01:43:20.353 --> 01:43:22.662
and she will.

1250
01:43:22.713 --> 01:43:25.181
It is a mathematical certainty.

1251
01:43:28.473 --> 01:43:30.464
How much time?

1252
01:43:36.273 --> 01:43:37.786
An hour...

1253
01:43:37.833 --> 01:43:39.949
Two at most.

1254
01:43:44.513 --> 01:43:47.266
And how many aboard. Mr Murdoch?

1255
01:43:47.313 --> 01:43:49.781
2.200 souls on board. sir.

1256
01:43:56.353 --> 01:43:59.550
Well. I believe you may get
your headlines. Mr Ismay.

1257
01:44:16.434 --> 01:44:20.632
Oh. it is a little slut. isn't it?
Look at me when I'm talking to you!

1258
01:44:21.994 --> 01:44:24.189
- Mr Hockley?
- Not now! We're busy!

1259
01:44:24.234 --> 01:44:26.748
Sir. please put on your lifebelt...

1260
01:44:26.794 --> 01:44:29.627
I said not now.

1261
01:44:29.674 --> 01:44:33.792
I'm sorry but it's Captain's orders.
Now. please. dress warmly.

1262
01:44:33.834 --> 01:44:36.064
It's quite cold out tonight.

1263
01:44:36.114 --> 01:44:38.469
May I suggest topcoats and hats?

1264
01:44:38.514 --> 01:44:40.505
This is ridiculous.

1265
01:44:41.274 --> 01:44:45.347
Not to worry. miss.
I am sure it's just a precaution.

1266
01:44:45.394 --> 01:44:47.544
Everybody up! Lifebelts on!

1267
01:44:48.994 --> 01:44:50.507
What's he on about?

1268
01:44:50.554 --> 01:44:52.909
- Lifebelts on!
- What's the ruckus?

1269
01:44:52.954 --> 01:44:54.672
Just put your lifebelts on!

1270
01:44:54.754 --> 01:44:57.063
CQD?

1271
01:44:57.114 --> 01:44:58.911
Sir?

1272
01:44:59.194 --> 01:45:02.425
That's right. CQD. The distress call.

1273
01:45:02.514 --> 01:45:04.152
That's our position.

1274
01:45:07.994 --> 01:45:11.873
Tell whoever responds
that we're going down by the head

1275
01:45:11.914 --> 01:45:14.792
and need immediate assistance.

1276
01:45:22.594 --> 01:45:24.391
Blimey!

1277
01:45:33.994 --> 01:45:36.508
Keep lowering! Keep lowering!

1278
01:45:55.994 --> 01:45:57.473
Mr Wilde!

1279
01:45:57.514 --> 01:45:59.470
Where are the passengers?

1280
01:45:59.514 --> 01:46:04.144
We moved them back inside.
It's too damn cold and noisy for them.

1281
01:46:05.474 --> 01:46:07.385
Help with these lines!

1282
01:46:21.154 --> 01:46:23.145
Care for a drink. sir?

1283
01:46:24.554 --> 01:46:28.342
Hey. sonny. what's doing?
You got us all trussed up here

1284
01:46:28.394 --> 01:46:32.706
- and now we're cooling our heels.
- Sorry. ma'am. Let me find out.

1285
01:46:32.754 --> 01:46:35.746
I don't think anybody knows
what the hell's going on.

1286
01:46:35.794 --> 01:46:39.150
It's the goddamned English
doing everything by the... book.

1287
01:46:39.194 --> 01:46:41.424
There's no need for language. Mr Hockley.

1288
01:46:41.474 --> 01:46:45.945
Go and turn the heaters on in our rooms.
I'd like a cup of tea when I return.

1289
01:46:45.994 --> 01:46:47.666
Yes. ma'am.

1290
01:46:49.354 --> 01:46:52.266
This ship has 15 watertight barricades.

1291
01:46:52.314 --> 01:46:55.784
Would you put your lifebelt on. please?

1292
01:46:56.194 --> 01:46:57.263
Mr Andrews...

1293
01:46:59.434 --> 01:47:03.029
I saw the iceberg.
and I see it in your eyes.

1294
01:47:03.074 --> 01:47:05.542
Please tell me the truth.

1295
01:47:12.114 --> 01:47:14.105
The ship will sink.

1296
01:47:14.554 --> 01:47:16.510
You're certain?

1297
01:47:16.554 --> 01:47:18.749
Yes. In an hour or so

1298
01:47:19.194 --> 01:47:22.982
all this will be
at the bottom of the Atlantic.

1299
01:47:23.034 --> 01:47:24.626
What?

1300
01:47:24.674 --> 01:47:29.270
Tell only who you must. I don't want
to be responsible for a panic.

1301
01:47:29.314 --> 01:47:31.953
And get to a boat quickly. Don't wait.

1302
01:47:31.994 --> 01:47:35.031
You remember what I told you
about the boats?

1303
01:47:37.994 --> 01:47:39.712
Yes...

1304
01:47:40.794 --> 01:47:42.546
I understand.

1305
01:47:50.194 --> 01:47:51.946
Over here. sir.

1306
01:47:51.994 --> 01:47:56.385
Sir. they need you in the second-class
purser's office. There's a mob up there.

1307
01:47:56.434 --> 01:48:00.393
- Go on. I'll keep an eye on him.
- Aye. Right.

1308
01:48:12.714 --> 01:48:16.946
Sir! Carpathia says
they're making 17 knots.

1309
01:48:16.994 --> 01:48:19.713
Full steam for them. sir.

1310
01:48:19.754 --> 01:48:22.905
- She's the only one responding?
- The only one close. sir.

1311
01:48:22.954 --> 01:48:24.831
They can be here in four hours.

1312
01:48:24.874 --> 01:48:26.910
Four hours?!

1313
01:48:31.714 --> 01:48:33.705
Thank you. Bride.

1314
01:48:37.154 --> 01:48:39.145
My God...!

1315
01:48:46.314 --> 01:48:47.827
Sir!

1316
01:48:47.874 --> 01:48:50.263
We are swung out and ready. sir.

1317
01:48:50.314 --> 01:48:54.910
Hadn't we better get the women
and children into the boats. sir?

1318
01:48:56.714 --> 01:48:58.432
Yes. we...

1319
01:48:58.474 --> 01:48:59.702
Sir?

1320
01:49:02.194 --> 01:49:04.389
Women and children first.

1321
01:49:04.434 --> 01:49:06.186
Yes.

1322
01:49:06.234 --> 01:49:08.225
Yes. sir.

1323
01:49:09.834 --> 01:49:13.304
Ladies and gentlemen.
your attention. please!

1324
01:49:13.354 --> 01:49:16.107
Step this way. please! That's right.

1325
01:49:16.154 --> 01:49:18.190
Come towards me!

1326
01:49:18.234 --> 01:49:20.065
Thank you.

1327
01:49:20.114 --> 01:49:21.069
Good.

1328
01:49:21.154 --> 01:49:25.432
For the time being I shall require
only women and children.

1329
01:49:25.474 --> 01:49:27.465
Right here.

1330
01:49:27.514 --> 01:49:29.664
Like the Captain said.

1331
01:49:29.714 --> 01:49:32.387
nice and cheery so there's no panic.

1332
01:49:32.434 --> 01:49:34.390
"Wedding Dance."

1333
01:49:41.474 --> 01:49:44.352
Lifebelts on!
Put your lifebelts on!

1334
01:49:44.394 --> 01:49:45.907
Put your lifebelts on!

1335
01:49:45.954 --> 01:49:49.344
Here. put your lifebelt on.
Here. come on...

1336
01:49:54.914 --> 01:49:57.667
It isn't time to go up
to the boats yet.

1337
01:49:57.714 --> 01:49:59.670
Please stay calm.

1338
01:49:59.714 --> 01:50:03.389
Look. please make sure
you've got your lifebelts on.

1339
01:50:03.434 --> 01:50:05.664
Women and children to the front.

1340
01:50:05.714 --> 01:50:07.705
What are we doing. Mummy?

1341
01:50:07.754 --> 01:50:12.544
When the first-class people
are in the boats. they'll start with us

1342
01:50:12.594 --> 01:50:14.425
and we'll want to be ready.

1343
01:50:16.634 --> 01:50:18.670
Go and get some help.

1344
01:50:18.714 --> 01:50:21.353
Lower away! Left and right together!

1345
01:50:21.394 --> 01:50:22.793
Steady!

1346
01:50:22.834 --> 01:50:24.950
Both sides together!

1347
01:50:24.994 --> 01:50:26.347
Steady!

1348
01:50:26.394 --> 01:50:27.793
Steady!

1349
01:50:27.834 --> 01:50:29.904
Steady!

1350
01:50:29.954 --> 01:50:32.024
Stop! Stop!

1351
01:50:33.394 --> 01:50:34.668
Hold the left side!

1352
01:50:34.714 --> 01:50:37.433
Right side only! Right side only!

1353
01:50:37.474 --> 01:50:38.873
Right side only!

1354
01:50:38.914 --> 01:50:40.313
Hold the left side!

1355
01:50:40.354 --> 01:50:42.868
Right side down!
Lower away together!

1356
01:50:44.514 --> 01:50:46.505
Steady. lads!

1357
01:51:32.114 --> 01:51:35.823
You know. I do believe this ship may sink.

1358
01:51:35.914 --> 01:51:41.068
I've been asked to give you this
small token of our appreciation.

1359
01:51:44.154 --> 01:51:46.748
Compliments of Mr Caledon Hockley.

1360
01:51:52.754 --> 01:51:55.905
Come on. sister. you heard the man.
Into the boat.

1361
01:51:55.954 --> 01:52:01.187
- Any room for a gentleman. gentlemen?
- Only women at this time. sir.

1362
01:52:01.234 --> 01:52:05.227
Will the lifeboats be seated
according to class?

1363
01:52:06.674 --> 01:52:09.507
I hope they're not too crowded.

1364
01:52:09.554 --> 01:52:13.342
Oh. Mother... Shut up!
Don't you understand?!

1365
01:52:13.394 --> 01:52:17.831
The water is freezing and there aren't
enough boats! Not enough by half.

1366
01:52:17.874 --> 01:52:21.264
Half the people on this ship
are going to die.

1367
01:52:21.314 --> 01:52:23.350
Not the better half.

1368
01:52:23.394 --> 01:52:25.828
Come on. Ruth. get in the boat.

1369
01:52:25.874 --> 01:52:28.547
First-class seats are right up here.

1370
01:52:28.594 --> 01:52:32.667
It's a pity I didn't keep that drawing.
It'll be worth more by morning.

1371
01:52:32.714 --> 01:52:36.548
Women and children towards the front.

1372
01:52:36.594 --> 01:52:38.744
You unimaginable bastard.

1373
01:52:39.634 --> 01:52:43.912
Come on. Rose. darling.
There's plenty of room for you.

1374
01:52:43.954 --> 01:52:47.993
- Come on. Rose. You're next.
- Come into the boat. Rose.

1375
01:52:48.834 --> 01:52:50.347
Come.

1376
01:52:50.394 --> 01:52:52.191
Rose!

1377
01:52:52.994 --> 01:52:54.985
Get into the boat!

1378
01:52:55.034 --> 01:52:57.025
Rose...

1379
01:52:57.434 --> 01:52:59.345
Goodbye. Mother.

1380
01:53:01.034 --> 01:53:02.626
Rose?

1381
01:53:02.674 --> 01:53:05.188
Where are you going?

1382
01:53:05.234 --> 01:53:07.111
To him?!

1383
01:53:07.154 --> 01:53:09.463
To be a whore to a gutter rat?!

1384
01:53:09.514 --> 01:53:12.187
I'd rather be his whore than your wife!

1385
01:53:14.354 --> 01:53:15.867
No... No!

1386
01:53:16.994 --> 01:53:19.189
I said no!

1387
01:53:19.234 --> 01:53:20.952
Rose!

1388
01:53:20.994 --> 01:53:22.905
Please stop!

1389
01:53:22.954 --> 01:53:25.912
- And lower away!
- Rose!

1390
01:53:25.954 --> 01:53:28.263
- Man the tiller!
- No. wait!

1391
01:53:28.314 --> 01:53:30.589
Rose!

1392
01:53:30.634 --> 01:53:32.750
Hold the left side there!

1393
01:53:35.554 --> 01:53:36.669
Help!

1394
01:53:36.714 --> 01:53:39.786
Can anybody hear me!

1395
01:53:39.834 --> 01:53:42.746
Hello. help me!

1396
01:53:42.794 --> 01:53:44.785
Help me!

1397
01:53:45.954 --> 01:53:48.422
Help me! Can anybody hear me!

1398
01:53:48.474 --> 01:53:51.068
Somebody help me!

1399
01:53:52.394 --> 01:53:54.385
Mr Andrews!

1400
01:53:56.914 --> 01:53:59.109
Check the starboard corridor.

1401
01:53:59.154 --> 01:54:02.226
Madam. please. put on a lifebelt.

1402
01:54:02.274 --> 01:54:06.347
Lucy. for God's sake. put on
your lifebelt. Set a good example.

1403
01:54:06.394 --> 01:54:07.463
Anyone in here?

1404
01:54:07.514 --> 01:54:12.110
Mr Andrews. thank God! Where would
they take someone under arrest?

1405
01:54:12.154 --> 01:54:14.827
You have to get to a boat right away.

1406
01:54:14.874 --> 01:54:19.186
I'm doing this with or without your help.
but without will take longer.

1407
01:54:19.994 --> 01:54:25.352
Take the elevator to the very bottom.
Go left down the crewmen's passage.

1408
01:54:25.394 --> 01:54:29.512
Go right and left again at the stairs.
You'll come to a corridor.

1409
01:54:33.274 --> 01:54:35.265
This could be bad.

1410
01:54:39.194 --> 01:54:40.866
Oh. shit.

1411
01:54:40.914 --> 01:54:42.427
Oh. shit!

1412
01:54:46.874 --> 01:54:48.387
Excuse me!

1413
01:54:48.434 --> 01:54:51.426
- The lifts are closed.
- I do not care...

1414
01:54:51.474 --> 01:54:52.873
The lifts are...

1415
01:54:52.914 --> 01:54:56.953
I'm sorry. miss.
but the lifts are closed.

1416
01:54:56.994 --> 01:55:00.987
I'm through being polite. goddamn it!
Now take me down!

1417
01:55:01.274 --> 01:55:02.627
"E" deck.

1418
01:55:06.194 --> 01:55:08.708
Come on... Come on. come on...

1419
01:55:25.394 --> 01:55:26.827
I'm going back up!

1420
01:55:26.874 --> 01:55:28.023
No!

1421
01:55:28.074 --> 01:55:29.268
No! No!

1422
01:55:29.314 --> 01:55:31.464
Miss. wait!

1423
01:55:32.314 --> 01:55:35.067
Come back! I'm going back up!

1424
01:55:35.114 --> 01:55:36.308
I'm going back up!

1425
01:55:45.114 --> 01:55:47.105
Crew passage...

1426
01:55:47.434 --> 01:55:49.425
Crew passage.

1427
01:56:08.354 --> 01:56:09.867
Jack!

1428
01:56:13.034 --> 01:56:14.752
Jack!

1429
01:56:18.834 --> 01:56:20.233
Jack!

1430
01:56:20.594 --> 01:56:22.585
Rose!

1431
01:56:23.394 --> 01:56:24.713
Jack!

1432
01:56:24.754 --> 01:56:26.312
Rose. I'm in here!

1433
01:56:26.354 --> 01:56:28.265
- I'm in here!
- Jack!

1434
01:56:28.314 --> 01:56:29.667
I'm in here!

1435
01:56:29.714 --> 01:56:30.942
- Jack!
- Rose!

1436
01:56:30.994 --> 01:56:32.712
Jack! Jack!

1437
01:56:32.754 --> 01:56:33.789
I'm sorry!

1438
01:56:33.834 --> 01:56:35.825
I'm sorry! I'm so sorry!

1439
01:56:37.154 --> 01:56:40.942
- Lovejoy put it in my pocket.
- I know! I know. I know. I know!

1440
01:56:40.994 --> 01:56:43.906
Rose. you have to find
a spare key. all right?

1441
01:56:43.954 --> 01:56:45.387
Look in that cabinet.

1442
01:56:46.634 --> 01:56:49.102
It's a little silver one. Rose.

1443
01:56:49.154 --> 01:56:50.872
Silver...

1444
01:56:50.914 --> 01:56:52.552
These are all brass!

1445
01:56:52.594 --> 01:56:54.903
Check right here. Rose.

1446
01:56:58.074 --> 01:56:59.712
Rose...

1447
01:57:00.714 --> 01:57:02.830
How did you find out I didn't do it?

1448
01:57:02.874 --> 01:57:04.865
I didn't.

1449
01:57:05.074 --> 01:57:07.747
I just realised I already knew.

1450
01:57:09.034 --> 01:57:11.309
Keep looking!

1451
01:57:17.754 --> 01:57:19.312
No key.

1452
01:57:19.354 --> 01:57:22.266
- There's no key!
- Rose. listen.

1453
01:57:22.314 --> 01:57:24.111
You have to go find help.

1454
01:57:24.154 --> 01:57:25.667
It'll be all right.

1455
01:57:30.834 --> 01:57:32.586
I'll be right back.

1456
01:57:38.754 --> 01:57:41.063
I'll just wait here.

1457
01:57:53.794 --> 01:57:56.149
Hello. is there anyone here?

1458
01:57:56.554 --> 01:57:58.033
Hello?

1459
01:57:58.074 --> 01:58:00.634
Is there anybody down here?

1460
01:58:01.154 --> 01:58:03.065
We need help! Hello!

1461
01:58:03.114 --> 01:58:04.866
Damn it!

1462
01:58:11.794 --> 01:58:15.673
Can anybody hear me! Please!
Hello! Hello!

1463
01:58:16.434 --> 01:58:18.265
Oh. thank God!

1464
01:58:18.314 --> 01:58:22.148
I need your help. There's a man
back here and... Wait!

1465
01:58:26.674 --> 01:58:28.551
Hello?

1466
01:58:51.914 --> 01:58:53.552
Hello?

1467
01:58:53.594 --> 01:58:58.145
- Miss. you shouldn't be here now.
- Please. I need your help.

1468
01:58:58.194 --> 01:59:01.152
There is a man down here
and he is trapped!

1469
01:59:01.194 --> 01:59:03.230
- No need to panic.
- I'm not panicking!

1470
01:59:03.274 --> 01:59:06.869
You're going the wrong way!
Let go of me! Listen!

1471
01:59:11.914 --> 01:59:13.666
To hell with you.

1472
01:59:35.514 --> 01:59:37.505
Lower away!

1473
01:59:43.674 --> 01:59:45.665
Oh. God...

1474
01:59:49.674 --> 01:59:51.665
Oh. my God...

1475
02:00:37.714 --> 02:00:39.352
Jack!

1476
02:00:39.394 --> 02:00:41.112
Rose!

1477
02:00:41.154 --> 02:00:43.145
Will this work?

1478
02:00:44.034 --> 02:00:46.673
I guess we'll find out. Come on.

1479
02:00:48.914 --> 02:00:50.950
Wait. wait. wait. wait!

1480
02:00:50.994 --> 02:00:52.791
Try some practice swings.

1481
02:00:57.754 --> 02:01:01.383
Good. Try to hit the same mark
again. Rose. You can do it.

1482
02:01:07.674 --> 02:01:10.142
Okay. That's enough practice.

1483
02:01:10.194 --> 02:01:11.946
Come on. Rose. You can do it.

1484
02:01:11.994 --> 02:01:15.987
Listen. just hit it really hard
and really fast.

1485
02:01:17.514 --> 02:01:20.233
Wait!
Open your hands up a little more.

1486
02:01:20.274 --> 02:01:22.549
- Like that?
- Right.

1487
02:01:22.594 --> 02:01:25.313
Listen. Rose... I trust you.

1488
02:01:29.434 --> 02:01:31.345
Go!

1489
02:01:35.914 --> 02:01:37.393
You did it!

1490
02:01:37.434 --> 02:01:39.868
Come on. let's go!

1491
02:01:39.914 --> 02:01:42.269
Oh. shit. this is cold! Oh. shit!

1492
02:01:42.314 --> 02:01:44.066
Shit! Shit!

1493
02:01:48.954 --> 02:01:50.353
This is the way out.

1494
02:01:50.394 --> 02:01:54.148
We have to find another way. Come on.

1495
02:01:54.194 --> 02:01:55.263
Pull!

1496
02:01:57.034 --> 02:01:58.103
Pull!

1497
02:01:58.154 --> 02:02:00.588
Put your backs into it! Pull!

1498
02:02:04.914 --> 02:02:06.472
Pull!

1499
02:02:06.514 --> 02:02:10.302
Now there's something
you don't see every day.

1500
02:02:30.714 --> 02:02:34.866
What's this luggage doing here?
Get rid of it! We need the room!

1501
02:02:40.034 --> 02:02:41.672
Keep calm!

1502
02:02:42.714 --> 02:02:46.104
Move along there. Make more room.
That's right. Look sharp.

1503
02:02:48.114 --> 02:02:50.947
- Lovejoy!
- She's not on the starboard side.

1504
02:02:50.994 --> 02:02:55.510
We're running out of time and this
martinet isn't letting any men on.

1505
02:02:55.554 --> 02:02:58.022
There's one on the other side
letting men on.

1506
02:02:58.074 --> 02:03:02.590
Then that's our play. We'll need
some insurance first. Come on.

1507
02:03:04.554 --> 02:03:06.749
This way. All the way down here.

1508
02:03:08.674 --> 02:03:11.984
Here! What do you think you're doing?

1509
02:03:12.034 --> 02:03:15.743
You'll have to pay for that!
That's White Star Line property!

1510
02:03:15.794 --> 02:03:17.068
Shut up!

1511
02:03:18.594 --> 02:03:22.951
Will you hold the boat a moment?
I just have to run back to my room...

1512
02:03:22.994 --> 02:03:25.144
Sit down!

1513
02:03:25.194 --> 02:03:29.187
Mr Lightoller. why are the boats
being launched half full?

1514
02:03:29.234 --> 02:03:33.546
- Not now. Mr Andrews.
- 20 or so in a boat built for 65

1515
02:03:33.594 --> 02:03:35.869
and I saw one boat with only 12! 12!

1516
02:03:35.914 --> 02:03:40.351
We weren't sure of the weight.
Mr Andrews. These boats may buckle.

1517
02:03:40.394 --> 02:03:41.429
Rubbish!

1518
02:03:41.474 --> 02:03:44.352
They were tested in Belfast
with 70 men!

1519
02:03:44.394 --> 02:03:48.592
Now fill these boats. Mr Lightoller.
for God's sake. man!

1520
02:03:53.874 --> 02:03:56.752
I need more women and children. please!

1521
02:04:00.514 --> 02:04:03.950
Get back in there.
This is not an exit.

1522
02:04:03.994 --> 02:04:07.623
- Get back in there.
- This is not an exit!

1523
02:04:08.034 --> 02:04:11.868
You can't keep us locked in here!
The ship's bloody sinking!

1524
02:04:11.914 --> 02:04:13.905
Bring forward the women!

1525
02:04:13.954 --> 02:04:15.945
Unlock the gates.

1526
02:04:16.794 --> 02:04:18.671
Women only!

1527
02:04:18.714 --> 02:04:20.466
No men!

1528
02:04:20.514 --> 02:04:22.311
No men!

1529
02:04:26.114 --> 02:04:28.105
Get back!

1530
02:04:30.434 --> 02:04:32.345
Lock the gates!

1531
02:04:32.394 --> 02:04:35.192
Get them back from those gates!

1532
02:04:35.234 --> 02:04:37.145
Don't touch the gates!

1533
02:04:39.674 --> 02:04:43.030
There are women and children down here!

1534
02:04:43.074 --> 02:04:45.588
Let us up so we can have a chance!

1535
02:04:45.634 --> 02:04:47.625
Get back!

1536
02:04:49.954 --> 02:04:51.512
- Jack!
- Tommy!

1537
02:04:51.554 --> 02:04:53.749
- Can we get out?
- It's hopeless that way!

1538
02:04:53.794 --> 02:04:55.466
Whatever we do.
we've gotta do it fast.

1539
02:04:55.514 --> 02:04:56.913
Jack!

1540
02:04:56.954 --> 02:04:58.512
Fabrizio!

1541
02:04:58.554 --> 02:05:00.351
The boats are all gone.

1542
02:05:00.394 --> 02:05:03.466
- This whole place is flooding.
- There is niente this way.

1543
02:05:03.514 --> 02:05:06.108
All right. Let's go this way. Come on.

1544
02:05:10.954 --> 02:05:12.785
I make my own luck.

1545
02:05:12.834 --> 02:05:14.790
So do I.

1546
02:05:22.354 --> 02:05:23.912
Come on!

1547
02:05:23.954 --> 02:05:26.070
No. come on. Let's go this way.

1548
02:05:34.314 --> 02:05:35.906
This way!

1549
02:05:35.954 --> 02:05:39.742
Go back to the main stairwell
and everything will be sorted out there.

1550
02:05:39.794 --> 02:05:41.113
The hell it will!

1551
02:05:41.154 --> 02:05:43.145
It will get sorted out back there.

1552
02:05:43.194 --> 02:05:44.547
Go back to the main stairwell.

1553
02:05:44.594 --> 02:05:46.903
- Open the gate.
- Go back...

1554
02:05:46.954 --> 02:05:50.026
- Open the gate now!
- Go back down the main stairwell!

1555
02:05:51.914 --> 02:05:55.031
Goddamn it! Son of a bitch!

1556
02:05:55.074 --> 02:05:56.507
Open the damn gate!

1557
02:05:56.554 --> 02:05:58.749
Go back!

1558
02:06:00.594 --> 02:06:04.587
- Fabri. Tommy. Give me a hand here!
- Move aside! Move aside!

1559
02:06:04.634 --> 02:06:06.272
Pull!

1560
02:06:07.114 --> 02:06:09.105
- Move aside!
- Put that down!

1561
02:06:09.194 --> 02:06:10.468
Move aside!

1562
02:06:10.514 --> 02:06:12.948
- One! Two!
- Stop that!

1563
02:06:12.994 --> 02:06:14.188
Three!

1564
02:06:16.274 --> 02:06:17.309
Again!

1565
02:06:19.194 --> 02:06:20.229
Let's go!

1566
02:06:21.714 --> 02:06:22.988
Let's go. Rose.

1567
02:06:23.074 --> 02:06:26.350
You can't go up there!
You can't do this!

1568
02:06:30.794 --> 02:06:33.752
Keep order! Keep order here!

1569
02:06:33.794 --> 02:06:36.866
Back! Back! Back!

1570
02:06:40.794 --> 02:06:42.193
Hold on to her!

1571
02:06:43.634 --> 02:06:44.953
Pull her in!

1572
02:06:44.994 --> 02:06:47.952
Get back. I say!

1573
02:06:47.994 --> 02:06:50.224
Or I'll shoot you all like dogs!

1574
02:06:50.274 --> 02:06:52.265
Keep order here!

1575
02:06:52.754 --> 02:06:54.824
Keep order. I say.

1576
02:06:55.274 --> 02:06:58.072
Mr Lowe. man this boat.

1577
02:07:01.834 --> 02:07:04.268
Is everybody all right?

1578
02:07:04.314 --> 02:07:06.191
Nobody panic.

1579
02:07:11.474 --> 02:07:13.351
Stay back!

1580
02:07:13.394 --> 02:07:16.591
- We're too late.
- There are more boats at the front.

1581
02:07:16.634 --> 02:07:20.263
Stay with this one.
Murdoch seems to be quite practical.

1582
02:07:33.954 --> 02:07:35.831
Sit down!

1583
02:07:36.314 --> 02:07:38.305
Stay back. you lot.

1584
02:07:38.394 --> 02:07:41.670
Stay back! Stay back.
the lot of you! Stay back!

1585
02:07:42.714 --> 02:07:46.707
It's starting to fall apart.
We don't have much time.

1586
02:07:47.754 --> 02:07:49.745
Mr Murdoch?

1587
02:07:49.874 --> 02:07:50.989
Mr Hockley...

1588
02:07:51.074 --> 02:07:52.507
You two. with me. now!

1589
02:07:52.554 --> 02:07:56.342
I'm a businessman. as you know.
and I've a business proposition for you.

1590
02:07:56.394 --> 02:07:59.830
Easy now! All together!

1591
02:07:59.874 --> 02:08:02.786
Lower away! Lower away!

1592
02:08:02.834 --> 02:08:04.825
Come on. Rose.

1593
02:08:07.554 --> 02:08:09.545
The boats are gone!

1594
02:08:13.114 --> 02:08:15.867
Colonel. are there any boats
on that side?

1595
02:08:15.914 --> 02:08:19.793
No. miss. but there are a couple
of boats all the way forward.

1596
02:08:25.314 --> 02:08:29.023
What's the use?
Nobody's listening to us. anyway.

1597
02:08:29.074 --> 02:08:31.872
They don't listen to us at dinner. either.

1598
02:08:31.914 --> 02:08:33.870
Come on. let's play. Keep us warm.

1599
02:08:33.914 --> 02:08:35.666
"Orpheus."

1600
02:08:39.594 --> 02:08:42.825
Music to drown by.
Now I know I'm in first class!

1601
02:08:47.794 --> 02:08:51.343
- Where is everyone?
- They're all still aft. sir.

1602
02:08:53.234 --> 02:08:56.146
We have an understanding. then.
Mr Murdoch?

1603
02:09:11.394 --> 02:09:14.511
Women and children only!

1604
02:09:14.554 --> 02:09:16.988
Get back! Step back. sir.

1605
02:09:17.154 --> 02:09:20.066
Come through. madam.
This way. Step back. sir.

1606
02:09:20.114 --> 02:09:22.753
You better check the other side.

1607
02:09:22.794 --> 02:09:24.386
Go!

1608
02:09:26.074 --> 02:09:31.273
Any more women and children?
Any children?

1609
02:09:31.314 --> 02:09:34.863
I found her on the other side
waiting for a boat.

1610
02:09:34.994 --> 02:09:36.347
With him.

1611
02:09:36.394 --> 02:09:39.943
- Any more women and children?
- They're all aboard.

1612
02:09:39.994 --> 02:09:42.064
Anyone else. then!

1613
02:09:42.114 --> 02:09:44.947
- Anyone else!
- Hurry along.

1614
02:09:48.474 --> 02:09:50.430
Stand by the falls.

1615
02:09:50.474 --> 02:09:53.432
Oh. goddamn it all to hell!

1616
02:09:55.194 --> 02:09:56.593
Shit!

1617
02:09:56.634 --> 02:09:58.352
Fire!

1618
02:09:58.394 --> 02:10:01.033
Sir! Sir. you can't go through here.

1619
02:10:01.074 --> 02:10:03.065
Sir. you can't go through.

1620
02:10:04.394 --> 02:10:06.908
Yes. yes. splendid. Right.

1621
02:10:07.954 --> 02:10:09.626
Right.

1622
02:10:10.114 --> 02:10:12.867
Prepare to lower!

1623
02:10:14.834 --> 02:10:16.825
Ready on the left.

1624
02:10:21.474 --> 02:10:23.465
Take them down.

1625
02:10:27.674 --> 02:10:29.665
Keep it steady.

1626
02:10:30.954 --> 02:10:33.548
Both sides together. Steady...

1627
02:10:33.914 --> 02:10:36.064
Keep it steady.

1628
02:10:36.394 --> 02:10:37.793
Give her to me.

1629
02:10:37.874 --> 02:10:38.989
Daddy...

1630
02:10:39.154 --> 02:10:42.464
It'll be fine. darling.
Don't you worry.

1631
02:10:42.594 --> 02:10:45.950
It's goodbye for a little while.
Only a little while.

1632
02:10:45.994 --> 02:10:50.624
There's another boat for daddies.
This one's for mummies and children.

1633
02:10:50.674 --> 02:10:53.234
Hold mummy's hand and be a good girl.

1634
02:10:53.274 --> 02:10:56.471
- I'm not going without you.
- You have to... Now!

1635
02:10:56.514 --> 02:10:57.503
No. Jack.

1636
02:10:57.554 --> 02:11:00.227
- Get in the boat. Rose.
- No. Jack.

1637
02:11:00.314 --> 02:11:02.111
Get on the boat!

1638
02:11:02.154 --> 02:11:04.509
Yes. get on the boat. Rose.

1639
02:11:06.594 --> 02:11:09.825
My God. look at you.
You look a fright!

1640
02:11:09.874 --> 02:11:11.432
Here.

1641
02:11:12.394 --> 02:11:14.191
Put this on.

1642
02:11:14.234 --> 02:11:15.792
Come.

1643
02:11:19.834 --> 02:11:23.747
- Go on. I'll get the next one.
- No! Not without you!

1644
02:11:23.834 --> 02:11:27.873
I'll be fine. I'm a survivor. all right?
Don't worry about me.

1645
02:11:27.914 --> 02:11:29.393
Now go on. get on.

1646
02:11:29.434 --> 02:11:33.188
I have an arrangement
with an officer on the ship.

1647
02:11:33.234 --> 02:11:35.509
Jack and I can get off safely.

1648
02:11:35.554 --> 02:11:36.669
See?

1649
02:11:36.714 --> 02:11:39.592
- Got my own boat to catch.
- Hurry!

1650
02:11:39.634 --> 02:11:41.192
They're almost full.

1651
02:11:42.554 --> 02:11:44.545
Step aboard. miss.

1652
02:11:45.994 --> 02:11:48.189
Step aboard. please.

1653
02:11:48.274 --> 02:11:51.311
Keep back. Keep back. I say!

1654
02:11:51.994 --> 02:11:53.985
Clear the row. please.

1655
02:11:55.634 --> 02:11:56.862
Lower away!

1656
02:12:00.194 --> 02:12:01.513
Slowly...

1657
02:12:01.754 --> 02:12:03.824
Keep going. keep going.

1658
02:12:04.114 --> 02:12:06.582
And lower away evenly. lads.

1659
02:12:06.714 --> 02:12:09.706
Easy... Lower away.

1660
02:12:09.754 --> 02:12:11.426
You're a good liar.

1661
02:12:11.474 --> 02:12:13.465
Almost as good as you.

1662
02:12:13.554 --> 02:12:16.864
Easy now... and lower away.

1663
02:12:17.994 --> 02:12:21.987
There's no. uh...
There's no arrangement. is there?

1664
02:12:22.034 --> 02:12:24.104
No. there is.

1665
02:12:24.474 --> 02:12:27.068
Not that you'll benefit much from it.

1666
02:12:28.754 --> 02:12:30.745
I always win. Jack.

1667
02:12:30.874 --> 02:12:32.865
One way or another.

1668
02:12:35.274 --> 02:12:37.265
Easy...

1669
02:12:38.674 --> 02:12:40.585
Even. lads.

1670
02:12:40.674 --> 02:12:43.063
Keep going. keep going.

1671
02:13:28.754 --> 02:13:29.709
Rose!

1672
02:13:32.674 --> 02:13:34.824
- Stop her!
- What are you doing!

1673
02:13:34.874 --> 02:13:36.751
Stop her!

1674
02:13:36.794 --> 02:13:38.193
No!

1675
02:13:55.474 --> 02:13:57.271
Rose!

1676
02:13:59.714 --> 02:14:02.706
You're so stupid! Why'd you do that?

1677
02:14:02.754 --> 02:14:04.745
You're so stupid. Rose!

1678
02:14:05.914 --> 02:14:08.109
Why did you do that? Why?

1679
02:14:08.514 --> 02:14:10.470
You jump. I jump. right?

1680
02:14:11.474 --> 02:14:13.066
Right.

1681
02:14:15.234 --> 02:14:17.509
Oh. God. I couldn't go.

1682
02:14:17.554 --> 02:14:19.545
I couldn't go. Jack.

1683
02:14:19.594 --> 02:14:22.631
It's all right.
We'll think of something.

1684
02:14:22.674 --> 02:14:24.949
At least I'm with you.

1685
02:14:37.274 --> 02:14:38.423
Come on!

1686
02:14:40.114 --> 02:14:41.467
Come on!

1687
02:14:41.514 --> 02:14:43.630
Come on! Move!

1688
02:14:49.634 --> 02:14:51.147
Come on!

1689
02:14:58.114 --> 02:14:59.513
Move!

1690
02:15:06.074 --> 02:15:08.952
Come on. Rose. Come on.

1691
02:15:09.794 --> 02:15:11.785
Rose. come on!

1692
02:15:13.594 --> 02:15:14.583
Move. Rose!

1693
02:15:17.394 --> 02:15:18.270
Go!

1694
02:15:28.674 --> 02:15:32.303
I hope you enjoy your time together!

1695
02:15:44.874 --> 02:15:47.263
What could possibly be funny?

1696
02:15:48.394 --> 02:15:50.954
I put the diamond in the coat

1697
02:15:52.714 --> 02:15:55.103
and I put the coat on her!

1698
02:15:55.634 --> 02:15:57.272
Come on!

1699
02:16:19.514 --> 02:16:21.505
We can't leave him.

1700
02:16:24.434 --> 02:16:26.345
All right. come on!

1701
02:16:43.194 --> 02:16:44.422
Go back!

1702
02:16:54.114 --> 02:16:56.992
It's the wrong way! Come back!

1703
02:17:03.154 --> 02:17:04.872
Go!

1704
02:17:20.754 --> 02:17:22.233
Jack!

1705
02:17:22.274 --> 02:17:23.673
Rose!

1706
02:17:35.394 --> 02:17:37.112
This way!

1707
02:17:45.154 --> 02:17:46.792
Come on.

1708
02:17:46.954 --> 02:17:48.592
Give me your hand.

1709
02:17:57.594 --> 02:17:59.266
Oh. God!

1710
02:18:02.434 --> 02:18:03.867
Help!

1711
02:18:08.834 --> 02:18:10.631
Help!

1712
02:18:12.514 --> 02:18:16.109
- Wait. sir! Open the gate. please!
- Help us. please!

1713
02:18:16.154 --> 02:18:17.553
Help us!

1714
02:18:17.594 --> 02:18:18.868
Please!

1715
02:18:18.954 --> 02:18:20.023
Please!

1716
02:18:20.154 --> 02:18:21.587
Bloody hell!

1717
02:18:24.834 --> 02:18:26.267
Hurry!

1718
02:18:27.434 --> 02:18:29.823
Come on! Come on!

1719
02:18:29.874 --> 02:18:31.466
- Go!
- Jesus...

1720
02:18:31.514 --> 02:18:33.789
- Please!
- Come on!

1721
02:18:33.834 --> 02:18:35.233
Hurry!

1722
02:18:35.274 --> 02:18:36.832
Come on!

1723
02:18:41.074 --> 02:18:43.144
I'm sorry. I dropped the keys!

1724
02:18:44.194 --> 02:18:46.185
Wait! Please!

1725
02:18:46.514 --> 02:18:49.233
Don't leave! Please! Get more help!

1726
02:19:06.794 --> 02:19:09.433
I got 'em! Which one is it. Rose?

1727
02:19:09.474 --> 02:19:11.908
The sharp one. try the sharp one.

1728
02:19:12.034 --> 02:19:13.149
Hurry. Jack.

1729
02:19:16.914 --> 02:19:18.506
Oh. no!

1730
02:19:18.594 --> 02:19:20.073
Hurry. Jack.

1731
02:19:22.434 --> 02:19:24.425
It's stuck!

1732
02:19:25.234 --> 02:19:27.225
Hurry. Jack!

1733
02:19:32.954 --> 02:19:36.310
I got it! I got it! Go! Go. Rose!

1734
02:19:36.354 --> 02:19:37.833
Go! Go!

1735
02:19:47.114 --> 02:19:48.342
Jack!

1736
02:19:49.074 --> 02:19:51.634
Jack! Come on!

1737
02:19:53.154 --> 02:19:55.270
Move! Move!

1738
02:20:01.954 --> 02:20:03.945
Keep on rocking!

1739
02:20:03.994 --> 02:20:06.383
Oars in place! Get an oar under it!

1740
02:20:06.434 --> 02:20:09.631
Women and children only. damn you!

1741
02:20:09.674 --> 02:20:12.268
Hold it! Hold it!

1742
02:20:22.914 --> 02:20:27.590
Get these davits cranked in!
Then get the falls hooked up!

1743
02:20:36.154 --> 02:20:38.145
Stay back!

1744
02:20:38.954 --> 02:20:41.184
Mommy...!

1745
02:20:47.474 --> 02:20:49.465
Keep going up!

1746
02:20:51.434 --> 02:20:53.152
Stop pushing!

1747
02:20:54.914 --> 02:20:56.506
Stay back!

1748
02:20:56.554 --> 02:20:59.148
Give us a chance to live.
you limey bastard!

1749
02:20:59.194 --> 02:21:01.662
I'll shoot any man
who tries to get past me!

1750
02:21:01.714 --> 02:21:02.908
Bastard!

1751
02:21:03.034 --> 02:21:04.149
Get back!

1752
02:21:04.194 --> 02:21:05.786
We had a deal. damn you.

1753
02:21:08.674 --> 02:21:12.508
Your money can't save you
any more than it can save me.

1754
02:21:12.554 --> 02:21:14.033
Get back!

1755
02:21:14.074 --> 02:21:16.793
Women and children only!

1756
02:21:23.634 --> 02:21:24.953
No! Tommy...

1757
02:21:24.994 --> 02:21:27.064
Bastardo!

1758
02:21:27.114 --> 02:21:30.311
Oh. no! Oh. no...!

1759
02:21:30.354 --> 02:21:33.869
Oh. no...! Tommy...!

1760
02:21:43.834 --> 02:21:44.869
No!

1761
02:21:50.874 --> 02:21:52.865
Stand back. damn you!

1762
02:22:08.354 --> 02:22:10.345
I have a child!

1763
02:22:10.394 --> 02:22:12.544
- I have a child!
- Clear a path here!

1764
02:22:12.634 --> 02:22:15.273
Please. I have a child!

1765
02:22:15.314 --> 02:22:18.226
Please. I'm all she has in the world.

1766
02:22:18.274 --> 02:22:20.265
Go on.

1767
02:22:21.114 --> 02:22:22.706
Step back!

1768
02:22:22.754 --> 02:22:24.745
Here. give her to me.

1769
02:22:27.874 --> 02:22:29.830
Give her here.

1770
02:22:31.154 --> 02:22:32.985
There. there.

1771
02:22:36.074 --> 02:22:37.792
Wait. wait. wait.

1772
02:22:37.834 --> 02:22:39.631
Mr Andrews...

1773
02:22:40.834 --> 02:22:42.233
Rose.

1774
02:22:43.794 --> 02:22:46.354
Won't you even make a try for it?

1775
02:22:48.714 --> 02:22:53.504
I'm sorry that I didn't build you
a stronger ship. young Rose.

1776
02:22:53.714 --> 02:22:55.352
It's going fast.

1777
02:22:55.394 --> 02:22:57.066
We have to move.

1778
02:22:57.114 --> 02:22:58.706
Wait.

1779
02:23:00.194 --> 02:23:02.185
Good luck to you. Rose.

1780
02:23:03.834 --> 02:23:05.586
And to you.

1781
02:23:16.314 --> 02:23:20.273
Mr Guggenheim...
These are for you. Mr Guggenheim.

1782
02:23:20.314 --> 02:23:21.793
No. thank you.

1783
02:23:21.914 --> 02:23:26.112
We are dressed in our best and
are prepared to go down as gentlemen.

1784
02:23:26.154 --> 02:23:27.872
But we would like a brandy.

1785
02:23:38.794 --> 02:23:40.307
Capitan.

1786
02:23:40.354 --> 02:23:42.743
Capitan. where should I go?
Please...

1787
02:23:47.234 --> 02:23:49.225
Captain!

1788
02:23:49.274 --> 02:23:51.834
Captain... Sir.

1789
02:24:20.794 --> 02:24:23.513
Right... That's it. then.

1790
02:24:23.554 --> 02:24:26.307
Goodbye. Wally. Good luck.

1791
02:24:26.354 --> 02:24:28.345
So long. old chap.

1792
02:25:39.274 --> 02:25:44.302
And so they lived happily together
for 300 years

1793
02:25:44.354 --> 02:25:47.232
in the land of Tir Na Nog.

1794
02:25:47.274 --> 02:25:50.346
Land of eternal youth and beauty.

1795
02:26:23.034 --> 02:26:25.343
There's no time!

1796
02:26:25.394 --> 02:26:28.909
Cut those falls!
Cut 'em! Cut 'em if you have to!

1797
02:26:28.954 --> 02:26:32.071
I need a knife! I need a knife!

1798
02:26:34.554 --> 02:26:36.784
Cut her loose!

1799
02:26:47.354 --> 02:26:49.265
Cut those bloody falls!

1800
02:27:34.154 --> 02:27:39.069
Gentlemen. it has been a privilege
playing with you tonight.

1801
02:28:36.714 --> 02:28:40.502
We have to stay on the ship
as long as possible! Come on!

1802
02:28:50.994 --> 02:28:53.554
This way. Over the rail!

1803
02:28:55.474 --> 02:28:57.908
Come on. Rose. Jump!

1804
02:29:00.514 --> 02:29:02.106
Come on!

1805
02:29:32.714 --> 02:29:35.182
I got you. Jump!

1806
02:29:36.554 --> 02:29:38.545
I've got you. miss!

1807
02:29:39.634 --> 02:29:41.226
Jack!

1808
02:29:42.594 --> 02:29:44.232
Get back!

1809
02:30:12.434 --> 02:30:14.425
No! You'll swamp us!

1810
02:30:26.634 --> 02:30:29.706
Though I walk through
the valley of the shadow of death...

1811
02:30:29.754 --> 02:30:32.587
You wanna walk a little faster
through that valley?!

1812
02:30:54.034 --> 02:30:55.626
Row!

1813
02:30:55.674 --> 02:30:57.665
Pull together!

1814
02:31:19.914 --> 02:31:22.382
Holy Mary. Mother of God.

1815
02:31:22.434 --> 02:31:25.983
pray for us sinners now
and at the hour of our death. Amen.

1816
02:31:26.034 --> 02:31:27.467
Hail Mary. full of grace...

1817
02:31:27.514 --> 02:31:29.391
This way.

1818
02:31:37.034 --> 02:31:38.626
Come on!

1819
02:31:38.674 --> 02:31:40.471
Come on!

1820
02:31:49.274 --> 02:31:51.390
I saw a new heaven and a new earth

1821
02:31:51.434 --> 02:31:55.552
when the first heaven and
the first earth had passed away

1822
02:31:55.594 --> 02:31:57.824
and there was no more sea.

1823
02:32:03.394 --> 02:32:07.512
It'll be over soon.
It'll all be over soon.

1824
02:32:11.754 --> 02:32:15.633
And he shall dwell with them
and they shall be his people

1825
02:32:15.674 --> 02:32:18.268
and God himself shall be with them.

1826
02:32:20.554 --> 02:32:22.385
Jack.

1827
02:32:22.434 --> 02:32:25.232
this is where we first met.

1828
02:32:31.194 --> 02:32:34.630
And God shall wipe away
all the tears from their eyes.

1829
02:32:34.674 --> 02:32:36.710
And there shall be no more death.

1830
02:32:36.754 --> 02:32:39.666
Neither shall there be sorrow or crying.

1831
02:32:39.714 --> 02:32:43.104
Neither shall there be any more pain

1832
02:32:43.154 --> 02:32:46.305
for the former world has passed away.

1833
02:32:59.514 --> 02:33:01.948
Bloody pull faster. and pull!

1834
02:33:24.194 --> 02:33:25.707
Hang on. Miss Trudy!

1835
02:33:53.594 --> 02:33:57.030
Help me! Please. save me!

1836
02:33:59.074 --> 02:34:00.189
Help!

1837
02:34:00.234 --> 02:34:02.225
Hold on real tight!

1838
02:34:18.154 --> 02:34:19.553
God Almighty!

1839
02:34:27.314 --> 02:34:30.386
Get those breakers in!
Keep 'em in!

1840
02:35:45.314 --> 02:35:47.305
We have to move!

1841
02:35:52.394 --> 02:35:55.306
Give me your hand.
I'll pull you over.

1842
02:35:55.354 --> 02:35:57.914
Give me your hand!

1843
02:35:57.954 --> 02:36:00.912
I've got you. I won't let go.

1844
02:36:00.954 --> 02:36:03.343
Come on. I've got you!

1845
02:36:12.634 --> 02:36:15.785
- What's happening. Jack?
- I don't know!

1846
02:36:24.474 --> 02:36:26.465
- Hold on!
- Jack!

1847
02:36:26.514 --> 02:36:29.187
Help me. please!

1848
02:36:29.314 --> 02:36:30.872
Someone help me!

1849
02:36:52.834 --> 02:36:55.792
Please help! Help!

1850
02:37:05.994 --> 02:37:07.393
This is it!

1851
02:37:18.754 --> 02:37:21.314
Oh. God! Oh. God!

1852
02:37:21.354 --> 02:37:23.424
Hold on!

1853
02:37:23.634 --> 02:37:26.228
Oh. God! Oh...

1854
02:37:38.034 --> 02:37:40.309
The ship is gonna suck us down.

1855
02:37:40.354 --> 02:37:42.584
Take a deep breath when I say.

1856
02:37:46.754 --> 02:37:49.905
Kick for the surface
and keep kicking.

1857
02:37:49.954 --> 02:37:52.707
Do not let go of my hand.

1858
02:37:58.634 --> 02:38:01.432
We're gonna make it. Rose. Trust me.

1859
02:38:01.514 --> 02:38:03.709
I trust you.

1860
02:38:06.314 --> 02:38:09.511
Ready? Ready?

1861
02:38:09.594 --> 02:38:11.312
Now!

1862
02:38:45.474 --> 02:38:47.305
Jack! Jack!

1863
02:38:47.354 --> 02:38:49.345
Jack!

1864
02:38:50.874 --> 02:38:52.432
Jack!

1865
02:38:56.914 --> 02:38:58.393
Jack!

1866
02:38:58.554 --> 02:39:00.112
Jack!

1867
02:39:17.434 --> 02:39:20.107
Jack! Jack!

1868
02:39:23.674 --> 02:39:24.629
No!

1869
02:39:25.874 --> 02:39:27.432
Jack!

1870
02:39:27.474 --> 02:39:29.430
Rose!

1871
02:39:29.794 --> 02:39:32.103
Get off her! Get off her!

1872
02:39:34.434 --> 02:39:36.868
- Rose!
- Jack!

1873
02:39:36.914 --> 02:39:39.303
Swim. Rose! I need you to swim!

1874
02:39:42.394 --> 02:39:44.510
Keep swimming!

1875
02:39:48.114 --> 02:39:50.708
- It's so cold!
- Swim. Rose!

1876
02:39:55.274 --> 02:39:57.663
Come on... here...

1877
02:39:57.994 --> 02:40:00.189
Keep swimming... come on.

1878
02:40:02.514 --> 02:40:04.869
Here. get on it.

1879
02:40:04.994 --> 02:40:06.985
Get on top.

1880
02:40:13.474 --> 02:40:15.465
Come on. Rose.

1881
02:40:24.634 --> 02:40:26.306
Stay on it. Rose.

1882
02:40:26.354 --> 02:40:27.753
Jack...

1883
02:40:46.754 --> 02:40:48.745
You'll be all right now.

1884
02:40:50.834 --> 02:40:52.825
You'll be all right now.

1885
02:40:58.794 --> 02:41:00.785
Return

1886
02:41:00.834 --> 02:41:02.552
the boats!

1887
02:41:05.594 --> 02:41:10.031
The boats are coming back for us. Rose.
Hold on just a bit longer.

1888
02:41:10.074 --> 02:41:13.384
They... had to row away
from the suction

1889
02:41:13.434 --> 02:41:15.994
but... now they'll be coming back.

1890
02:41:16.034 --> 02:41:18.832
Come back!

1891
02:41:18.874 --> 02:41:23.311
- For God's sake!
- Please! Help us!

1892
02:41:25.114 --> 02:41:27.628
Come back! For God's sake!

1893
02:41:27.714 --> 02:41:32.993
You don't understand. If we go back.
they'll swamp the boat!

1894
02:41:33.034 --> 02:41:37.312
- They'll pull us right down!
- Knock it off. You're scaring me.

1895
02:41:37.354 --> 02:41:39.584
Come on. girls. grab an oar.

1896
02:41:39.634 --> 02:41:43.343
Are you mad?! We're in the middle
of the North Atlantic!

1897
02:41:43.394 --> 02:41:47.103
Do you people want to live
or do you want to die!

1898
02:41:53.194 --> 02:41:55.788
I don't understand a one of you.

1899
02:41:56.994 --> 02:41:59.303
What's the matter with you?!

1900
02:41:59.354 --> 02:42:01.743
It's your men out there!

1901
02:42:01.794 --> 02:42:06.549
- There's plenty of room for more.
- There'll be one less on this boat

1902
02:42:06.594 --> 02:42:10.109
if you don't shut that hole in your face!

1903
02:42:10.194 --> 02:42:13.550
Come back!

1904
02:42:23.394 --> 02:42:24.986
Take this one.

1905
02:42:25.034 --> 02:42:29.824
Bring in your oars over there.
Tie these two boats together as well.

1906
02:42:33.114 --> 02:42:36.584
Now make sure that's tied up
nice and tight.

1907
02:42:38.954 --> 02:42:41.832
Listen to me. men.
we have to go back.

1908
02:42:41.874 --> 02:42:46.902
I want to transfer all the women
from this boat into that boat.

1909
02:42:46.954 --> 02:42:49.309
Let's get some space there.

1910
02:42:58.314 --> 02:43:00.874
It's getting quiet.

1911
02:43:02.034 --> 02:43:05.788
It's just gonna take 'em
a couple of minutes to get

1912
02:43:05.834 --> 02:43:08.189
the boats organised.

1913
02:43:10.394 --> 02:43:12.828
I don't know about you. but

1914
02:43:12.874 --> 02:43:17.868
I intend to write a strongly worded letter
to the White Star Line

1915
02:43:17.914 --> 02:43:19.905
about all this.

1916
02:43:25.594 --> 02:43:27.789
I love you. Jack.

1917
02:43:33.794 --> 02:43:35.785
Don't you do that.

1918
02:43:36.794 --> 02:43:39.866
Don't you say your goodbyes. Not yet.

1919
02:43:39.954 --> 02:43:41.910
Do you understand me?

1920
02:43:42.114 --> 02:43:44.105
I'm so cold.

1921
02:43:44.154 --> 02:43:46.031
Listen. Rose...

1922
02:43:46.074 --> 02:43:48.793
You're gonna get out of here.

1923
02:43:48.834 --> 02:43:53.908
You're gonna go on. and you're
gonna make lots of babies.

1924
02:43:53.954 --> 02:43:57.185
and you're gonna watch 'em grow.

1925
02:43:57.234 --> 02:43:59.225
You're gonna die an old

1926
02:43:59.274 --> 02:44:02.471
an old lady warm in her bed.

1927
02:44:03.154 --> 02:44:05.145
Not here.

1928
02:44:05.194 --> 02:44:08.550
Not this night. Not like this.

1929
02:44:08.594 --> 02:44:10.824
Do you understand me?

1930
02:44:13.234 --> 02:44:15.350
I can't feel my body.

1931
02:44:16.594 --> 02:44:22.032
Winning that ticket was the best thing
that ever happened to me.

1932
02:44:22.394 --> 02:44:24.385
It brought me to you

1933
02:44:25.394 --> 02:44:28.147
and I'm thankful for that. Rose.

1934
02:44:28.194 --> 02:44:30.185
I'm thankful.

1935
02:44:31.394 --> 02:44:34.067
You must... You must...

1936
02:44:35.594 --> 02:44:38.154
You must do me this honour...

1937
02:44:39.794 --> 02:44:43.548
You must promise me
that you'll survive...

1938
02:44:45.514 --> 02:44:47.948
that you won't give up.

1939
02:44:47.994 --> 02:44:50.303
no matter what happens...

1940
02:44:52.594 --> 02:44:54.983
no matter how hopeless.

1941
02:44:58.074 --> 02:45:00.065
Promise me now. Rose...

1942
02:45:01.994 --> 02:45:04.792
and never let go of that promise.

1943
02:45:05.634 --> 02:45:07.625
I promise.

1944
02:45:09.234 --> 02:45:11.225
Never let go.

1945
02:45:13.594 --> 02:45:15.789
I will never let go. Jack.

1946
02:45:18.194 --> 02:45:20.913
I'll never let go.

1947
02:45:42.394 --> 02:45:44.624
Right ahead. sir.

1948
02:45:47.354 --> 02:45:49.345
Oars!

1949
02:45:49.394 --> 02:45:51.624
Do you see any moving?

1950
02:45:51.674 --> 02:45:53.869
No. sir. None moving. sir.

1951
02:45:53.914 --> 02:45:55.905
Check them.

1952
02:45:56.474 --> 02:45:58.465
Bring that oar up here.

1953
02:46:02.474 --> 02:46:04.465
Check them. Make sure.

1954
02:46:05.994 --> 02:46:07.985
These are dead. sir.

1955
02:46:08.034 --> 02:46:09.626
Now give way.

1956
02:46:09.674 --> 02:46:11.471
Ahead easy.

1957
02:46:16.874 --> 02:46:19.149
Careful with your oars.

1958
02:46:19.194 --> 02:46:21.185
Don't hit them.

1959
02:46:22.554 --> 02:46:25.432
Is there anyone alive out there!

1960
02:46:25.954 --> 02:46:28.946
Can anyone hear me?

1961
02:46:29.954 --> 02:46:32.787
Is there anyone alive out there!

1962
02:46:38.714 --> 02:46:40.705
We waited too long.

1963
02:46:44.114 --> 02:46:47.470
We'll. keep checking them!
Keep looking!

1964
02:46:47.514 --> 02:46:50.392
Is there anyone alive out there!

1965
02:46:53.874 --> 02:46:55.990
Can anyone hear me!

1966
02:47:15.354 --> 02:47:18.630
And it's up she goes.

1967
02:47:18.674 --> 02:47:20.949
Up she goes.

1968
02:47:56.994 --> 02:47:58.552
Jack?

1969
02:48:02.474 --> 02:48:04.430
Jack.

1970
02:48:06.954 --> 02:48:09.184
Jack.

1971
02:48:15.434 --> 02:48:18.346
Jack... there's a boat.

1972
02:48:19.114 --> 02:48:20.911
Jack...

1973
02:48:31.034 --> 02:48:32.752
Jack?

1974
02:48:33.154 --> 02:48:35.031
Jack...

1975
02:48:36.034 --> 02:48:38.025
Jack!

1976
02:48:40.634 --> 02:48:42.625
Jack!

1977
02:48:44.354 --> 02:48:46.993
There's a boat. Jack.

1978
02:48:49.074 --> 02:48:51.065
Jack?

1979
02:49:28.274 --> 02:49:30.265
Come back.

1980
02:49:30.554 --> 02:49:32.226
Come back!

1981
02:49:34.154 --> 02:49:36.145
Come back!

1982
02:49:36.634 --> 02:49:38.192
Come back!

1983
02:49:38.234 --> 02:49:40.225
Come back!

1984
02:49:41.114 --> 02:49:43.423
Come back! Come back!

1985
02:49:44.674 --> 02:49:46.505
Hello!

1986
02:49:47.834 --> 02:49:50.394
Can anyone hear me!

1987
02:49:50.474 --> 02:49:52.942
There's nothing here. sir.

1988
02:49:54.434 --> 02:49:56.425
Come back!

1989
02:49:57.154 --> 02:49:59.145
Come back...

1990
02:50:05.554 --> 02:50:07.545
I'll never let go.

1991
02:50:07.594 --> 02:50:09.585
I promise.

1992
02:50:49.914 --> 02:50:51.905
Come about!

1993
02:51:12.554 --> 02:51:19.187
1.500 people went into the sea
when Titanic sank from under us.

1994
02:51:21.034 --> 02:51:24.822
There were 20 boats floating nearby

1995
02:51:25.274 --> 02:51:27.742
and only one came back.

1996
02:51:28.554 --> 02:51:30.306
One.

1997
02:51:31.954 --> 02:51:34.752
Six were saved from the water.

1998
02:51:34.794 --> 02:51:36.910
myself included.

1999
02:51:37.634 --> 02:51:42.469
Six... out of 1.500.

2000
02:51:45.034 --> 02:51:47.025
Afterward.

2001
02:51:47.554 --> 02:51:52.264
the 700 people in the boats
had nothing to do but wait.

2002
02:51:53.954 --> 02:51:57.344
Wait to die. wait to live...

2003
02:51:58.354 --> 02:52:00.549
Wait for an absolution

2004
02:52:00.594 --> 02:52:02.585
that would never come.

2005
02:53:02.554 --> 02:53:06.832
Sir. I don't think you'll find
any of your people down here.

2006
02:53:06.874 --> 02:53:08.865
It's all steerage.

2007
02:53:10.114 --> 02:53:14.710
His hair is reddish brown.
Reddish brown and a white beard.

2008
02:53:14.754 --> 02:53:18.713
- Is there another passenger list?
- There's no other list.

2009
02:53:18.754 --> 02:53:23.032
- Perhaps he's on another ship.
- We're doing all we can. ma'am.

2010
02:53:44.554 --> 02:53:47.352
That's the last time I ever saw him.

2011
02:53:47.394 --> 02:53:51.307
He married. of course.
and inherited his millions.

2012
02:53:51.354 --> 02:53:54.710
But the crash of '29
hit his interests hard

2013
02:53:54.754 --> 02:53:57.951
and he put a pistol
in his mouth that year.

2014
02:53:57.994 --> 02:54:00.713
Or so I read.

2015
02:54:11.594 --> 02:54:13.903
Can I take your name. please. love?

2016
02:54:16.954 --> 02:54:18.945
Dawson.

2017
02:54:20.194 --> 02:54:22.230
Rose Dawson.

2018
02:54:22.274 --> 02:54:24.265
Thank you.

2019
02:54:30.194 --> 02:54:34.745
We never found anything on Jack.
There's no record of him at all.

2020
02:54:34.794 --> 02:54:37.592
No. there wouldn't be. would there?

2021
02:54:37.914 --> 02:54:41.190
And I've never spoken of him until now.

2022
02:54:41.234 --> 02:54:43.225
Not to anyone.

2023
02:54:43.274 --> 02:54:45.788
Not even your grandfather.

2024
02:54:45.834 --> 02:54:49.429
A woman's heart
is a deep ocean of secrets.

2025
02:54:49.914 --> 02:54:53.987
But now you know there was
a man named Jack Dawson

2026
02:54:54.034 --> 02:54:56.070
and that he saved me.

2027
02:54:56.114 --> 02:54:59.663
In every way that a person can be saved.

2028
02:55:01.354 --> 02:55:03.993
I don't even have a picture of him.

2029
02:55:06.394 --> 02:55:09.989
He exists now only in my memory.

2030
02:55:14.514 --> 02:55:18.712
Keldysh. Keldysh.
Mir 2 on our way to the surface.

2031
02:55:33.234 --> 02:55:36.590
I was saving this
for when I found the diamond.

2032
02:55:45.514 --> 02:55:47.505
I'm sorry.

2033
02:55:49.754 --> 02:55:54.145
Three years I've thought
of nothing except Titanic

2034
02:55:55.074 --> 02:55:57.065
but I never got it.

2035
02:55:59.714 --> 02:56:02.023
I never let it in.
